895854086620365486_265771455.caption: 8 weeks into my reverse diet and feeling grrrrrreat 😁😊🙌 Pics from this morning... STILL at the same weight & body fat % AGAIN #winning 😂 I hadnt been taking any circumference measurements, just started last week, but certain things are def fuller so im not complaining! 😳🍑 Reverse dieting is a slowwww process, but I've successfully cut my cardio in HALF, while have added over 300 calories per day to my diet. Yes I could increase food more & do minimal cardio, but this is what's working for ME; my goal is not to "bulk" (I really don't like that term anyways) really looking to maintain a fit & healthy look all year round 😏 I feel happy & confident in my skin 🙌 This week i decided my plan is actually to keep my food constant but lower my cardio/day; plus want to try some new foods & different combos. I realized I hadn't been eating enough during the day, & nutrient timing is important to some degree, so gotta work on making my meals a little bigger! 👏 I actually really like this process/reverse dieting; Im still learning more about my body, how different macros/foods affect me, etc...keeps me motivated & helps that post-contest "now what?" feelings! too! Overall workin on that balance & lowering my stress levels one day at a time! #happyandhealthy #fitgirlforlife #reversedieting #balancingact #mybestself

1085539367526967993_312987409.caption: I am a dog mom. I spoil our pups to no end, have endless conversations with them throughout the day, sleep with a paw in my back most nights, and have had the honest and raw sense of loss when I had to let my best friend go to wait for us on the other side. Sarah and I are very much cut from the same cloth, so to say we understand each other and the love we have for our four legged kiddos is an understatement. I had the true privilege of capturing her and Jordan's family just over a year ago - their beloved Sandy had been diagnosed with an aggressive cancer which took her leg, but she was the happiest little tri-pawd you would ever meet and she and her big "little" sister Ruby made us laugh till we cried during their session. Sandy lived every day to the fullest and was a pillar of strength for her family up until her very last day earlier this year. Sarah, Jordan, and I held it together for their family session last weekend - mostly because Ruby is such a ham, but I admittedly lost it when going through their images. Sarah found an image that she wanted to recreate and the moment I saw it I knew it had to be done. To me it speaks volumes and the fact that there are three "hands" supporting each other not only represents the love and support they give each other, I like to think it also perfectly represents the love and strength of their favorite tri-pawd, Sandy.

We've all been given promises. Promises that keep us hoping, that keep us pressing on. Maybe it's a relationship restored, a diagnosis miraculously turned around, a family United. We ALL have those promises deeply rooted in our  hearts.

The Lord is in the waiting. Drawing us closer. Singing lullabies over our hearts as the confirmations of the coming time come to sustain us.

Whatever it is you're waiting on today, know that He cares so deeply for you. He cares to soothe your heart in this waiting time, to KNOW you and for you to KNOW His love. Evil is NOT from Him. And it's NOT His sovereign will to ALLOW evil. That's NOT who the King is. No matter what you've been told or have experienced. KNOW this: He is FOR you (no matter what you've done), He longs to reveal His goodness to you in EVERY circumstance, and His LOVE for you is far greater than any ill word spoken against you.

I release JOY over you, I release the dreamers to dream, I release the army of lovers to arise. ❤️. Lean in and listen, His heart beats for YOU. #hope #inspire #jesus #Perfectlove #faith #believe #theone #hope #higher #joy #love #morelord

952943242867554205_18398756.caption:
We all have dreams, desires, and hopes. We ALL have a desire so deep in our hearts, a dream that seems too big to handle. May it be a dream to break the cycle of poverty, or a dream to see a COMPLETE restoration of a family. A DREAM should ALWAYS be bigger than yourself.
There is ONE who loves you more than you will ever know. One who created you and knows you better than you know yourself. The One who placed the dreams inside you, to watch you SOAR and FLY.

Today, you may be discouraged because of a dream that has been dormant in your heart, or even a dream or desire that didn't quite pan out as you would have hoped. BUT I want to encourage you, because as long as you have breath, ITS NOT OVER YET. . . .NOTHING is impossible for God. I BREAK fear off you today, I RELEASE you to DREAM, to HOPE, to BELIEVE. . . No matter how wild and big the dream is . .IT IS POSSIBLE. Dream BIG today. . DECLARING the parting of the "red seas" in your mind today and inviting you to think above and beyond logic or reason, to embrace the truth of how AMAZING, PRECIOUS, and UNIQUE you are in this world!!! <3 
#inspire #love #dream #hope #nothingsimpossible #reachhigher #faith #motivate

1092352690123510663_191209163.caption:
So I was back in my fave local haunt @healthyselfco this morning (eating my fave meal, the Nourish Bowl) when I decided to make a commitment whereby for the next 7 days I'd only eat when I am really hungry, and just see what happens. This might sound ridiculous to some, but I don't have a huge appetite & having had big issues previously with low blood sugar (& CFS/adrenal fatigue) I've grazed throughout the day, for fear of debilitating drops in energy. In some instances I have eaten (not hungry) pre excursions for fear of not having food for too long a period. 
Anyway, I've returned from the Indian #panchakarma retreat feeling the best I can remember feeling, even having fasted (& survived!). So watch this space, in fact join me if you feel like it. My bet is it will be at least 6-7 hours before I feel really hungry again today. Maybe I'll end up on only 2 meals a day..? #intuitiveeating #inspiration #theholisticingredient #yarraville #healthyselfco #melbournecafe #melbourne #plantbased

1139508972676561541_5999205.caption:
I had a ton of super ripe bananas 🍌🍌🍌 so I whipped up some banana bread! 🍞 It's gluten-free and dairy-free and you can make it vegan by using chia or flax egg substitute.
#glutenfree #dairyfree #bananabread  INGREDIENTS:
4 eggs or use flax/chia egg for vegan
2 cups very ripe mashed bananas (used 5 or 6 bananas)
1 cup sugar (I used coconut sugar)
½ cup unsweetened applesauce
1 tsp real vanilla extract
⅓ cup coconut oil
1-1/2 cups brown rice flour
½ cup sorghum flour or coconut flour
1 tsp baking soda
½ tsp salt (I also added some cinnamon and pumpkin pie spice)
**BAKE at 350 for 40 mins. So delicious!!! Comes out great every time! 😋😃🍌🍞🍌

653939473920736543_596377478.caption: This photo really motivates me to voice my views and beliefs that I would like to share. I believe that animals are beyond intelligent, caring, nurturing, and harmless....shouldn't we humans strive to be more like these beautiful animals and learn from them instead of brutally killing them? Cows 🐮, chickens, pigs 🐽 sheep etc deserve better, they deserve a life. They have been put on this earth just like us so how come we think we are above them? We need to respect them and care for them, and if your opinion is that they are undeveloped and 'stupid' than let them develop and grow and evolve- exactly the way we humans had the opportunity and privilege to. We need to bring them into a world of love and compassion, not of murder and slavery. Peace, love and harmony will not exist until we share the earth with these beautiful creatures as equals. 🙏 #equality #love #compassion #vegan #crueltyfree #respect

958902879198713380_421083908.caption: Hi #tiuteam. I have to share this because I'm so sad and disappointed. I recently read that some fellow #tiugirls had a very poor experience with a Beachbody coach that has turned their hearts from the entire company. They said they felt as though they were only a quick sale. PLEASE hear me when I tell you this is NOT the norm! Yes, I post about challenge groups and Shakeology, and I post about coaching, but NEVER to "make a sale". I host challenge groups for girls who need help being consistent and making healthy choices. I invite you to the coaching opportunity because it's changing my life right before my eyes, and I want others to experience that! I want to help those with a passion for health and fitness turn it into a career that's never truly work. Would you purchase something at some point? Probably, as it's hard to coach without product experience, but the sale is NEVER my goal. Nor is it the goal of most coaches. We want what's BEST for you, and if that doesn't mean our challenge group, we're cool with that! We want YOU to be happy and healthy first! Now, I say this with a lot of passion because it breaks my heart that ANY of you had a bad experience. If you feel like being a coach on a team that wants only to inspire, encourage, uplift and help others, please feel free to direct message me or comment below. This is NOT a sales pitch, and this is NOT in search of a quick sale. This IS for anyone who has questions about what coaching is about. I love you all, #tiuteam, and I want the world to feel your passion. Comment below if you have questions. ❤️

872766652780696442_1299934915.caption: Guys- @utahbirddogtraining would be so proud of me! My husband is a major hunter. We have had a plethora of wild game available to us since we got married. After a few rough experiences/smells- I had to put the stop on eating wild game- I just couldn't do it! 😝 Tyce always gave me a hard time about not eating it... He'd say stuff like "come-on! You want grass-fed don't you?!" Haha! Even still the meat would just get made into jerky- and everyone was happy! A few years ago reading in "Nourishing Traditions" and sitting next to Tyce, I came across this line: "If you are lucky enough to have a hunter in your family, or if you have access to fresh game, do take advantage of your good fortune and serve healthful game to your family as often as possible" I showed this line to Tyce and he's reminded me of it ever since!!😂 This year I told him if we paid the extra expense of getting it butchered and put in nice packages I'd try to be a better sport- so.... When Tyce put a roast in the crock-pot I new I had to suck it up and just eat it! I'm really not a picky water AT ALL but the thought... Ah! I don't know! Anyway- I am getting my roast beef fix and I'm not eating roast beef! It's yummy- and meat and potatoes, and spaghetti squash and butter were made for each other.

743834332708000580_1299934915.caption: Stopppppp! This bag of kettle corn is literally a long as my arm! 😝 it tastes good- and I've gotta try not to eat the whole thing! Whattya do when it's for a sports high school fundraiser?! One thing I've learned is that I really do have a very fine line for sugar tolerance. Sugar addict in the trenches here! I'm sure I'll always be in recovery- 😥 but I do feel it's important to find balance! After a few crazy days with plenty of treats it's amazing to see how fast that sugar monster reels his head! Feeling so sick and gross is just not worth it!

744267037794947081_1299934915.caption: Lunch was a win!! We had beets last week on a salad and no one touched them except me! • 3 big spoonfuls of plain yogurt

My Saturday I ended up in the ER. At 4:15 this morning I missed the last stair and fell and twisted my right ankle. We have had ice and snow this week so we wanted to wait until the ice cleared up before going. I was never too worried about the baby because I did not fall on my belly. I kind of rolled. I usually fall gracefully...... I've had practice because I'm a klutz. 
I ended up with a fractured Tibia. I can't put weight on it for another 2-3 weeks and worse I can't drive because it had to be my right leg. Grrrr. 
I did get to see the baby so maybe it is worth it 😃😃 she is fine, heartbeat great. #klutz #ivf3 #ivfpregnancy #ivfsuccess #momtobe

1106605699510551809_1140859080.caption:
I cannot believe I'm posting 3 month pics already.  12# 6 oz and 25 inches. Size 2 diapers and 3-6 month clothes. I'm so sad putting away some of her first outfits she wore the first few weeks. She has been such an easy baby I'm blessed! We've had our fussy days but overall she is such a happy baby. She loves to be mobile and look around at things and loves to watch TV. She sometimes is happier when we put her down to play instead of holding her 😢  she is talking allot now and smiles all the time.  I love it when she is eating and looks up at me and stops sucking for a second to let out a smile....melts my heart. 
I am proud I've made it 3 months breast feeding. This was my first goal to reach. It is going well but sadly I still don't love it like I should. I've been pumping more and using bottles allot more during the day. I'm such a detail type person I like knowing exactly how many ounces she is getting.  She does well going back and forth from bottle to breast. So my next goal is to make it to January EBF that's when I go back to work. After that we will see....I don't have the ideal office for pumping.  #3months #ivfsuccess #ivfpregnancy #ivf3 #ivf #sweetbay #allmine

Took a small spaghetti squash, cut it in half put it in a microwave safe dish face down with a small amount of water, microwaved for about ~8 minutes and voila! Topped it with a green bean tomato sauce that I had in the cabinet which was delicious! Moral of the story, don't let your ruined dinner get you down... Don't be afraid to improvise, you may find it comes out way more delicious than you expected! 😃 goodnight everyone! #oops #spaghettisquash #healthy #dinner #eatingwithadietitian #nutrition #food #easy #tomatosauce #yum

On Saturday, we moseyed around The Worker's Museum in #newtown. 
Did you know that Mary Fitzgerald square, which was a political and labour meeting place for black and white workers, was named after  female unionist "Pick handle Mary" in 1938? 
She organized wives and daughter of tram workers for various sit ins and strikes in the 1900s, recognizing that the industrial system, and the fabric of South African society, was built entirely on their compliance; and that non-compliance could yield a positive revolution and dignity in their workplaces.

This is @keenangrams learning more.

EASY 3 Ingredient Chocolate NICE CREAM. Organic, Gluten-Free & Dairy Free. So great for a nice treat to yourself or your kids!! (Serves 5 scoops)

INGREDIENTS: 
2 Frozen Organic Bananas 
3-4 tbsp organic cacao powder (depending how rich you want the chocolate taste) (I use @navitasnaturals) 
1 tsp organic cinnamon (I use @redapecinnamon) 
INSTRUCTIONS:

1. In a food processor, blend the frozen bananas, cinnamon and cacao powder to a fine purée or until completely smooth like a soft serve ice cream. 
2. Place the soft serve in a bowl and put in the freezer for four hours to harden like ice cream. You can choose to eat it as a soft serve but, but if you want actual ice cream scoops you must freeze for that duration.

10. Favorite horror actor, and actress?: Jamie Lee Curtis and Bruce Campbell ...
I'll keep this one short and sweet: I've always adored JLC since her iconic role in Halloween (which is also my favorite horror movie of all time). She's funny and seems to accept the fame that comes with the title as America's original Scream Queen (which some people aren't always comfortable with/receptive to). Bruce Campbell- he's an interesting character! Part cocky, and yet humble, he takes his fame as Ash in The Evil Dead in stride; doing conventions and immersing himself amongst the fans. Both of these actors are currently starring in their own respective shows- JLC in Scream Queens and BC in Ash vs Evil Dead! 🎃 #jamieleecurtis #brucecampbell #halloween #evildead #31daysofhalloween #octoberphotochallenge #favoriteactors

1093622438684421971_10397970.caption:
11. Favorite holiday themed movie?: "Gremlins" (1984) ...
Gremlins was a fantastic comedy film from 1984- the best year ever in my opinion for great movies. "Gremlins" is milestone movie-making magic, a simple idea like "Back to the Future," stretched out into a bigger picture. While it's not as complex as "Future" is, it doesn't need to be, and certainly doesn't want to be. It relies on humor and charm, and it has plenty of it. Everything Joe Dante touches is usually magic. Even his live-action/animation film "Toy Soldiers" was a load of fun because of its charming disposition. Dante doesn't try to make his films anything other than what they are - charming and wildly, wickedly funny - and that is undoubtedly the key to the outrageous success of "Gremlins," one of the biggest box office moneymakers ever released. Dark, chaotic and pretty darn infectious, the film's sense of humor quickly kicks into boot even during the campy voice-over narrative. The whole film is campy, endearing, fresh and funny and has a bunch of likable characters -- especially Gizmo, the favorite and most infamous little critter ever seen on screen. 🎃 #gremlins #joedante #31daysofhalloween #octoberphotochallenge #favoriteholidayhorrormovie

1148265413625599314_1061235340.caption:
Three months ago, we were finally able to stare into each other's eyes for the first time. Three whole months ago. I can hardly believe it. It's December 25th of 2015. You are asleep in your crib. Daddy and I are watching Across the Universe. Yesterday, it hit me. You are my life. Caring for you, loving you, and keeping you safe from harm. It's a lot to take on for a girl like me, but you are worth it. I try to relax while you sleep, but sometimes I just can't. I miss you. I lay there watching you, praying I am the mom I have always wanted to be. I silently review the day we have spent together so far, thinking of what I can do better. Only after I take in every ounce of your beauty can I fall asleep. I am so grateful for you. You're beautiful, inside and out. Your happiness is contagious. Thank you for smiling. Without you, in the midst of this major life change, I might forget how to. But you, you have the biggest smile. You have a sincere giggle that inspires me. Today you are three months old, and we could not be more excited to see what you learn during month four of your life. Thank you for being you, Z. You are so easy and fun to love. We love you.

I used a big handful of kale, an even bigger handful of basil and some watercress with just enough oil to cover #Nolansoliveoil and then 3 bulbs of garlic and the juice of a lemon. I also added some walnuts and pinenuts. Blend and done. Wills adores it on meat veges and zucchini noodles. Such a great way to add vitamins and nutrients.  The lady at the market suggested that I line my vege crisper with a dry towel, then pop in the produce then soak a towel in water and cover the veges and tuck them in like a baby so they are damp to help keep the greens fresh all week. I tried it last week and it kept them fresh the entire week and nothing was soggy or spoilt. The fridges aim is to draw out moisture so the idea of the wet /damp towel is to keep some moisture in. #organic #thrive #greens #healhisgut #easyquickfoodideas #mealsinminutes #healthybaby #healthyfamily #gfcf #madewithlove #bubbayumyum

641780524558192020_25575898.caption:
01-25-14: a grace borrowed, found, inherited
Time. It doesn't often occur to me, but we are all on borrowed time. Days like today, my Colt's 2nd birthday, give me cause to stop and recognize the ephemeral and transient nature of our time on Earth. Since becoming a mom, and more specifically since becoming a stay-home mom, it seems like the days last forever but the years fly by. My tiny baby girl turned one earlier this month and now, today, my little baby boy turned two. Time, especially borrowed time, is a gift to be treasured because you do not know how much of it you have; tomorrow is promised to no man. Watching my babies grow in the blink of an eye humbles me and convicts me of the need to treasure each moment, each stage, each tear, each smile; True love. I feel so sorry for those that spend their life never finding their true love here (to say nothing of missing out on the truest of love, His for each of us). My pity doesn't come from a place of moral superiority or a sense of personal accomplishment but rather from a place of sheer gratitude and awe that God would deem me worthy of such love here on Earth as that which I share with Mike. I am so thankful to have found him and I know that it was His hand leading the way; Laughter. It was, and still is, the soundtrack of my life (that and Chicago, but that's a whole 'nother story). Our house was always filled with laughter whether it was us and Mom being silly, Dad laughing at his own jokes, or sarcasm and teasing wit bandied about among the three of us girls. Nothing makes me happier than hearing my babies laugh with each other. There is no sound more magical than a baby's belly laugh, all out of breath and squealing. Pure music. I am so grateful that laughter is still consistently the most often heard sound on the phone, at my house, in my memories and my heart. #joydarechallenge2014 #jan25 #1000gifts

700121616860712880_25575898.caption:
OOPS, accidentally posted this pic for the wrong day. Here's the right one.  04-04-14: 3 gifts in His word
Peace. Reassurance. Knowledge. The Bible is full of many treasures and many gifts, not the least of which is the peace and reassurance that the knowledge of His love brings. John 3:16 has been my personal favorite since I was probably seven or eight years old, and remains such. It is the verse that sums it all up for me. Though there have been times when my faith wavered, when my sinful nature dominated, and when my walk with Him was distant at best, there has never been a time that I didn't feel peace and reassurance in knowing how great His love for me is. #joydarechallenge2014 #april4 #1000gifts #oops

659477373771451649_25575898.caption:
02-17-14: 3 gifts in giving and serving (late) 
Love. Service to others is an opportunity to truly show others God's love through your actions. Words are easy and anyone can say them but taking the time and effort to actually be a light isn't always easy (or convenient). Compassionate giving speaks volumes and often can reach areas mere words never could; Setting an example. I want my babies to grow up with giving hearts and joyful spirits. I want them to always give more than they take. How can I expect them to know the joy of serving others if I don't model it for them?; Living my faith. Indeed, this goes hand in hand with both love and setting an example but it bears the redundancy. After all, if you truly believe something and have faith in it, it naturally follows that you would live it #joydarechallenge2014 #feb17 #1000gifts

659028143638449233_25575898.caption:
02-14-14: 3 ways you feel the love of God (better late than never)
Friendships. God has blessed me with amazing, loving, supportive and inspiring friends. Childhood friends, work friends, church friends, new mommy friends--all of them a reflection of God's immense concern for me; Motherhood. The love you feel for your children is truly unlike any other in the world and mere words barely scratch the surface of explanation. At least ten times a day I find myself watching my babies--lump in my throat, robbed of breath--caught by pure, indescribable love. I cannot squeeze them hard enough or snuggle them close enough to ever truly communicate to them how fierce my love for them is. I thank God for them a million times over and know that my love for them, though so immense and strong, is a reflection of God's love for me; My loving husband. I could not have asked for a more amazing man to share my life with. He is sweet, affectionate, loving, generous, forgiving, brave, and just outright wonderful. But most importantly, he is filled with faith and love for God. He is my perfect better half and I thank God for putting him in my life. Mike's love for me is just one more piece of evidence of God's love for me #joydarechallenge2014 #feb14 #1000gifts

675675040658623741_25575898.caption:
03-10-14: 3 gifts in Christ
Grace. Because of His grace all my mistakes (and God knows they're many) serve a purpose instead of serving shame. Though I may stumble a million times, His grace will always catch me; Love. So much so that He gave His life for so that we may not perish; Redemption. The end-all be-all destination reached through the vehicle of His grace and love. #joydarechallenge2014 #march10 #1000gifts

644680849711566125_25575898.caption:
01-29-14: a song heard, a soft word, a light seen
"It's Me, Oh Lord (standing in the need of prayer)". Listening to Colt sing "it's me" over and over while pointing to himself makes me smile. I love knowing that the first songs he's learning the words to are praise songs; Whispered prayers. As I lay my babies to sleep, Mike's prayers as we go to bed--gratitude, hopes, and fears--all beautiful and all gifts; Moonlight. Colt is currently obsessed with the moon and every time we go outside he looks up and asks for the moon. He seems disappointed when I explain that it's daytime and the sun is out but the smile he graces me with when I point out the moon melts my heart. #joydarechallenge2014 #jan29 #1000gifts

633774540900405069_25575898.caption:
01-14-14: 3 ways you glimpsed the startling grace of God
People use the phrase, "There, but for the grace of God..." so often and so casually. I know I've uttered it on multiple occasions. But how often does the gut-wrenching meaning of such a simple sentiment truly strike you? Driving home from OC tonight with both babies and my mom we sat in dead-stop traffic in the Fastrac on-ramp for a solid 30 minutes. As finally caught a glimpse of the cause of the traffic, I found myself praying not just for the safety and comfort of whoever was in the mangled mess that was once a (two? three?) car, I also thanked Him that we weren't in one of those cars; Watching Colt excitedly point out the bright, beautiful moon to Papa just before leaving his house I was able to glimpse the awe and wonder of the creation that He, in His infinite generosity, gives us every day; Climbing into bed and snuggling up to my sleeping husband, I found myself contemplating how different my life would be without him. As he woke up just enough to say our nightly prayers, I was flooded with gratitude that God would give me such a wonderful man. All three of these gifts today reminded me, in such a tangible way, that, but for His grace, I would have nothing. #joydarechallenge2014 #jan14
#1000gifts

856726572013702930_457905242.caption:
Remember Victor?

Last month many of you donated to help 17 year old Victor return to school. He recently took his final exams for Grade 7 and did incredibly well! Victor placed 19 out of 73 students in his class.

Before arriving at the Ahadi Education Center Victor survived in Nairobi on rotten fruits and numerous amounts of different drugs until our team found him in the streets of Ngong. Victor’s willingness to change is unlike any boy we had ever seen before; he has an old soul, and a wild passion for knowledge and the unknown. He's currently writing poems weekly and is working on both a book and play. He has a dream to become a writer and a psychologist for children who have ended up in similar situations as him.

#thankyou #Education #school #book #Kenya #recovery #nonprofit #Uniform #smart

1098684720235548333_21024738.caption:
Today I have chosen to give myself a little credit. I'm so hard on me most times. Forgetting how far I've come. 
I have been beaten up, dragged ridiculed, abused sexually, mentally,emotionally, physically. I have been punched spit on and kicked when I was already down. I have been suicidal, homeless, battled depression and low self esteem. But I'm still here.
##

I have been taken advantage of, stolen from and forgotten by ppl I loved. Preyed upon when I was at my weakest. But I'm still here.
##
I had ppl working inside my brain 3 times, and still to this day I don't complain about the constant side effects I deal with or make excuses because I'm still here. 
##

Even when they told me I would have a hard time putting things together including words, phrases and completing thoughts. But surprise I ended up writing a book, creating tv shows, products and travel doing motivational speaking without flinching lol.  Because I'm still here.
##

I've flipped my truck upside down on a bridge and landed half way over a cliff and had to crawl out the window but I'm still here.
##
I've had a heart murmur with irregular heartbeats that stop and double up at random since I was in grade school and although I can't run long, I'm still here.
##
I have vertigo and get nauseated when things move, shake or bounce. Even something as simple as watching a movie but I'm still here.
##
I'm a single mom, who's child's father hasn't been around in years, But guess what we're still here.
##
I've done almost everything I've set out to do and I've completed it. 
Today although I've been led to sell everything that I've worked for, leave the beautiful house I prayed for, and most everything behind. I am going. Why? because I'm still here. 
##
Sometimes we have to ask ourselves why are we still here. There is a reason. There's so much more to do, to learn, to explore, to create, TO LIVE. 
Why can't I help turn a small village around with the incredible knowledge that I've gathered, film their mission, bring them more awareness, teach them, build there confidence, utilize my resources in the states to give them hope and the tools needed to thrive. Why can't I? When I'm still here. It's time.

After surviving his fall from the #WTC #KingKong is given an artificial heart (presumably by the same organisation that had just shot the shit out of him). Shifting from figurative to metaphorical #kong goes in search of #ladyKong, finds her and love blossoms. More great work from #DinoDeLaurentis and directed by #JohnGuillermin who's best work is #ToweringInferno. #KingKongLives #VHS #Vhyes #adventure #RomCom

1103056282446930701_410900199.caption: City of Blood (1987) A rare #VHS tape with an amazing cover. Sex workers are being killed and the most likely culprit is an ancient shaman who has risen from the dead. #AllHallowAllIn #Vhyes #horror #splatter #gore

890325998812471495_410900199.caption: Hog Wild (1980) #MichaelBiehn from #Terminator stars as a boy who returns home from military school to find his hometown being terrorised by a motorcycle gang and his high school sweetheart going out with their leader. I don't think he sleeps with his best friends mom in this one. #hogwild #vhs #comedy #vhyes. Back when ex-rental cost $10, what a world.

893661043753165082_410900199.caption: Return of the Evil Dead (1973) As this is the only #BlindDead film I own on tape, I thought I'd show you the back cover put together by Redemption. The film is the best of the four blind dead films. The slow motion galloping skeletons on horseback is such an enduring image in my mind. I love it. In this film the former Templar knights decide to crash a towns celebration and then they massacre just about everyone. The ending is tremendous as the sunrise makes them all freeze and our remaining heroes have to tiptoe past a town full of them. #AmandoDeOssorio #vhs #vhyes #horror #templarknights #spain

968981045506678985_410900199.caption: Teen Wolf (1986-1988) The Animated series. I've already posted one of these tapes but here's another couple of episodes. The cover points out the dichotomy of #ScottHoward's existence. He can play it straight in human form with #boof, or he can turn on the wolf and hang out with a seductive yellow haired person in a dangerous house where chickens go nuts. Which are you? The wolf? Or the straighty 180? #JamesHoward who plays the dad in the movies, provides his own voice for the show, because he's a good guy. Unlike #MichaelJFox who thought he was all #DocHollywood. #Teenwolf #horror #kids #animated #toon #cartoon #VHS #vhyes

962472259992363088_410900199.caption: I Was A Teenage Werewolf (1957) This the film that started the title trend "I was a...." A smash at the drive-in. Starring #MichaelLandon. The story of a teen who visits a doctor for hypnotherapy, but the doctor is a bit evil and turns him into a #werewolf. #horror #scifi #vhs #vhyes #iwasateenage #iwasateenagewerewolf

1011845072221840101_410900199.caption: Bloody Wednesday (1987) Based on the 1984 #spreekilling inside a Californian McDonalds, which lasted more then an hour and 22 people (including 5 children) died. In this movie there's no kids and the spree lasts five minutes. So it's no #MacAndMe, in that #McDonalds didn't sponsor it, but it does present an amazing portrait as the killer lives in an old old Haunted House amusement that is haunted by those who once worked there. #BloodyWednesday #TrueStory #VHS #vhyes

982011263704047932_410900199.caption: The Bogus Witch Project (2000) Life doesn't get much worse, then the time spent watching this tape. It's not a film. It's a mess. It's got 1.7 on #IMDB and I couldn't give it more then a one. It's a compilation of short parodies of #TheBlairWitchProject that have been shot on home video for a shitty LA film festival. Some of the parodies are the same but by different people. One of the parodies features #PaulyShore, that's him on the cover in the corner. #TheBogusWitchProject #Horror #comedy #VHS #vhyes

838298951034807021_410900199.caption: Killing Spree (1987) A man suspects his wife of #adultery and goes on a #killingspree, eliminating all he believes are sleeping with her, but his victims don't stay #dead. #horror #vhs #vhyes

833562811140612178_410900199.caption: Lone Wolf (1988) A struggling rock band and other college students cope with the trials and tribulations of their young lives and find themselves in the role of determining what exactly is behind the recent full-moon killings which have been attributed to wild dogs. #werewolf #lychen #wolf #lonewolf #horror #vhs #vhyes

887091102056915307_410900199.caption: Opera (1987) #DarioArgento nails this psychotic variation on the #PhantomOfTheOpera story. With a young singer stepping up the main role in Verdi's #Macbeth, her crazed fan starts killing everyone close to her so that he can have her all to herself. It features one of my favourite horror scenes, as the star has needles taped to her eyelids so she can't close them and is forced to watch her loved one murdered in front of her. Horrible. Apparently #Argento always joked that this is what he wished he could do to his audience so that they couldn't look away when there were murders in his films. Such a sweet man. #horror #vhs #vhyes #needles #eyes #opera

976298227139814242_410900199.caption: Evilspeak (1981) The title is derived from "Computer Speak" a phrase you don't hear much anymore. The story is of a loser cadet who uses his computer to summon #demons so that he can reap revenge on the academy. #horror #evilspeak #VHS #vhyes #computerspeak

1132195639908832749_15720196.caption: #Charlie the #Weim had a rest day today. He had major upset tummy issues this morning, which seem to be rooted in anxiety. He's eating boiled white rice, and chill'n with water to stay hydrated. In my experience, dogs that are bred for work, especially hunting, and herding breeds, tend to have intense anxiety issues, which tend to be more exaggerated and dramatic if the dog is essentially not given a job, other than being a very loved, spoiled family member. It's rough stuff to get over, and adhere to structure, but he'll come around. I have faith. Give your dog structure, coupled with a calm routine, and you will have a reliable #calmfamilydog. #GoodKarmaTraining #Weimaraner #weimsofinstagram #weimobsessed #ghosteyes

973399976573080622_15720196.caption: More direction, less affection. That is how I rehabilitate and train dogs. It's not that I don't enjoy petting dogs. I totally do. Petting dogs, talking to them in a #babyvoice, handing out #treats like kittens doesn't earn ya any #streetcred in the dog world. How do I know? I've tried it...and failed. Do I wish we could all live harmoniously with our dogs by pouring on thick layers of #affection? Hells yes I do! 😊 It doesn't work though. We all need to focus on providing our dogs with clear directions, if we plan on having genuine solid companionship. #fact #goodkarmatraining #calmfamilydog #doodle #goldenlab #goldenlabrador #doodles #doodlesofinstagram #labsofinstagram

973191614365840207_1035537699.caption:
"AFTER": @healthyhappy_chelsey

Chelsey, I absolutely LOVE the caption you wrote for this picture yesterday!

I've been thinking about it ever since I read it and I just wanted to take a moment to thank you.

You spoke with passion about how our culture has become obsessed with the "After" photo - that picture people take AFTER they've achieved their fitness goals.

You spoke about how we wait to love and celebrate ourselves until AFTER we look the way we want to look - even if that means looking like someone else.

We post pictures of celebrities and crushes (#WCW) who have the body or body parts that we wish for and we hold ourselves in a prison of devalued self worth until we start to look at least a little bit like them.

We wait, and wait and wait to love ourselves... until AFTER.

It never occurs to most of us that we are actually beautiful and extraordinary RIGHT NOW!

Chelsey, I completely agree when you say that it's okay and wonderful to pursue fitness goals but that we need to remember that we're beautiful all along the way!

There is no point in waiting to love ourselves. Life is slipping by.

The only true "After" is the one that happens when our hearts stop beating.

And we won't be around to post that picture and tag it for likes.

#ICanSeeYourBeauty
#NathanaelLark

993657670520201306_295868255.caption:
The City of Wichita was founded in 1868 and incorporated in 1870. Initially a trade confluence for cattle and goods on the Arkansas River, Wichita has grown to be the largest city in Kansas and 49th largest in the U.S., known for its festivals,  sunsets, famous founders and celebrities, and - increasingly in the past few years - its understated but bold flag. The name of the city and the flag draw from the lengthy and interesting history of the Wichita Indians, whose ~2,000 year past spawned many subsequent accredited tribes as well as advancements in the settlement of the entire Midwest. We wouldn't be here without their progress, and while there are still Wichita Natives to be found mostly in Oklahoma, it'd be great if Native Americans as a people weren't relegated to reservations.

Also, I'm from there, and I love to visually share my story and the greater story that's shaped it. S'like, my whole deal with tatts. #tattoo #freshink #wichita #historylesson 
Buhbye Wichita, I love you and I'll see you in December!

912114480832509328_1541315188.caption: This book was splendid. In the foreward, Plath's daughter, Frieda Hughes, gracefully demystifies the Sylvia/Ted conundrum, and helps to make sense as to why "Ariel" was not published to Plath's specifications the first time around. Of her mother, Hughes says, "She used every emotional experience as if it were a scrap of material that could be pieced together to make a wonderful dress." Frieda read "Ariel" for the first time in her life in order to put this collection together. She aims to make her mother's poetry more significant than her death. This collection not only lays out "Ariel" exactly as Plath intended, but also includes copies of her original manuscript pages--with early drafts! There is also a poem by Frieda included in the supplementary material. #sylviaplath #ariel #bookgrrrl #bookworm #booknerd #readmore #tiniestbookreview #igbookclub #booksbooksbooks #poetry #originalgothgirl

1133867358411224758_1541315188.caption: I first read this book when I was in that liminal space between teenagerdom and adulthood, teetering on the edge of a world filled with rent/electric bills/having no money left over for cigarettes, while still clutching my glitter eyeshadow and rollerskates. In 1998 (the year this book was published) I was finishing high school in small-town-bum-fuck Texas and preparing to fly (on fledgling wings) to NYC, the city of grandeur and wildness and buildings taller than I had ever seen. I was learning how to hide my pain in the same place that I hid my childhood—inaccessibly deep, locked tight, key thrown in the Atlantic--while misunderstanding the importance of self-awareness and self-love. I’m glad that I had this book with me on that journey—even though it ended up being a treacherous, shark-filled, sinking-skied, stinky-armpitted journey, I can’t even imagine how much worse it might have been if I didn’t have Francesca Lia Block’s words (all of her words, not just this book) as a guiding light, a healing tincture, a place to nest myself when the concrete underneath my feet had melted into a roiling pit of self-conscious misunderstanding and cheap beer. Reading this book now helped me to reconnect with the fairy that lives in my Vivienne Westwood handbag—she’s snarky and tough like Mab, but her hair is pink like construction-paper Valentines rather than “the darkest red oleander blossoms.” It also reminded me to follow my dreams, no matter how many creeping creeps get in the way. As humans (and fairies) we are made of malleable starstuff—we are always ripe for transformation. We can become Selena Moon or Teeny Winter or whoever we need to be in order to fly. Magical, imaginary, or as solid as stone, relationships with others can help us strengthen our wings. 💜 #francescaliablock #iwasateenagefairy #losangeles #bookworm #bookgrrrl #bookstagram #tiniestbookreview #readmore

938413187970915811_55795790.caption:
My phone died before I could post my Day 10 "Goals" photo for #AnAppleADayPhotoChallenge. I think that too often in the health and wellness sphere the focus is put in physical goals, those that focus on performance or appearance. There's NOTHING wrong with that, but when coupled with single-mindedness that borders on obsession, it makes for a flat personality. What about goals for character development, mental stimulation, greater generosity or challenging fears? Making sure we are caring for our whole person is tantamount to health. That's why I like to balance my fitness goals (I'm coming for you, strict body weight pull-ups and back squat PRs) with goals like this one: 
#
#
I've been working my way through First Lady Laura Bush's "25 Books to Read Before You're 25" list for about 10 years now. I'll be 25 in June and I've only got a few more months to check the last books off my to-read list! (Pictured are some of my favorites from the list.) This goal is more than just a reading list - to me it represents a long journey that has both shaped and been witness to the person I have become. To finally achieve this goal will be a huge accomplishment of mine. What are some of your goals you're working on? They can be big or small, what matters is what they mean to you.

945782780899494854_1252158201.caption:
There is magnificent power that I feel whenever I am around the ocean. The sheer size and vastness of its waters brings about a deep respect for all the life that it holds within.

As we boated along to Maya Bay, I counted dozens of plastic bottles and bags that were floating on the surface, carried by the currents. 
I couldn't help but feel a deep sadness for the ocean. The amount of rubbish that ends up in its waters due to human ignorance is staggering. 
I am grateful that we are beginning to see our impact on the world around us and that laws are being put in place to limit the amount of plastic that ends up in our ecosystem :)
📷: @mollyjosephla

K I N D N E S S // Image snagged from: @findinglouie, a lovely account. 
I would say "be kind ESPECIALLY to mean people". Easier said than done but the meanness you perceive in others is actually something the universe is trying to show you about yourself. Maybe you do that same thing you're seeing in them. Maybe you need to assume more power and stop feeling powerless (not the same as kindness). Sometimes we confuse kindness with being a doormat. Don't make that mixup. Stand up for yourself AND be good to others. Being mean, negative, judgmental, and rude can only bring more of the same into your life.

973209288944784511_1648117692.caption: Shizuoka City. This is an underpass of the Tomei, the toll highway between Tokyo and Nagoya. It is only on such a highway, elevated, apart from other roads, that frustrated Japanese drivers can cut loose and drive like hell and not be stopped and fined. Constrained in their daily lives, it must afford them a tremendous release. The Tomei is the one major barrier between a tsunami attack and my apartment and I am counting on it to blunt the force of the blow. I also keep a life preserver handy. All the way from Canada, as nothing my size is available here. I consider the under view of the bridge here a good example of unintended man-made industrial beauty. It also happens to be azalea season here too. #shizuoka #highway #japan #tsunami #azalea #flowers #explorejapan #instajapan #tidalwave #industrial #industrialbeauty #bridge #bridges #marginal #driving

984752766858172126_1648117692.caption: Tokyo, Near Tokyo Station, Yaesu. This man is cleaning his glasses. Outside out of almost all glasses stores in the country small machines like this are set up so that people can get the grease and grime off of their glasses. They are free. Probably one of the only free services in Japan. Public benches are few and far between because there is no ethic of providing places to sit for nothing. As far as the glasses stores go, they are probably hoping that either you will go in and buy another pair, or remember them in the future when you do decide to buy. So maybe the service isn't exactly free. There is an ulterior motive. My Shizuoka bank provides towels to dry off with on a rainy day, but that is only because I am a customer. Nonetheless, I cannot imagine a Canadian bank putting out clean towels for a frigging CUSTOMER! And if it did, those towels would be stolen so fast because most people feel so ripped off by their banks that having a chance to rip them off back would be most satisfying. #tokyo #tokyostreetview #glasses #cleaningglasses #japan #explorejapan #exploretokyo #freeinjapan #tokyostation #glassesstore #customerservices #publicrelations #instatokyo #instajapan #lovejapan

Meet this week’s DESIGNER DOG: Leif 
CS: Who are your humans?
Leif: Christine and Jens Nicolaysen 
CS: You’re a very well-mannered 8 year-old. How did you learn to be such a good citizen?
Leif: My dad, Jens, worked very hard with me when I was a young pup. Then my mom came along when I was already 3 for the easy part! 
CS: You sometimes get to come to the office with Christine. How do you like that?
Leif: It’s great! I usually go to work with dad and my brother Leo so it’s nice to have some time to myself with mom. 
CS: We asked you to put your paw on your favorite CS tile. You chose MADERA. Why?
Leif: MADERA is the best of both worlds, the durability and easy maintenance of tile and the beautiful look of wood! It’s perfect for all the days I come home with muddy paws but still want a beautiful floor. Woof woof!

1136993547967462358_2107020189.caption:
Meet this week’s DESIGNER DOG: STAR… a 6 year old Husky 
CS: Who are your humans?
Star: Brent & Moises are my humans.  Brent works at Fentress Architects and Moises works at Children’s Hospital. 
CS: You’re an adopted dog. How did you find your forever home? 
Star: I was running these streets until I got caught up and ended up in the shelter. Then these two strolled up one day and were so slayed by my good looks and diva personality that they became instant stans and I let them adopt me. 
CS: If you had to pick a favorite activity, what would it be?
Star: Lavishly lounging and entertaining party guests.  Even when I'm not the center of attention, I'm happy to remind my fans of my beautiful voice and variety of stage tricks because there is only one STAR in this house. 
CS: The LUXOR tile makes a beautiful backdrop for your photo. What made you choose it?
Star: I chose this tile because it reflects my Charisma, Uniqueness, Nerve, & Talent in more ways than one 😉

1075680613493947297_1580771325.caption: Fork and foam sheet/cork Flower making in my Afternoon Art Class. This class is a little less art oriented and more craft-type things, which, if I'm being honest, is a bit weird and out of my comfort range for me. I spend 99% of my time as a teacher preaching the virtues of "process over product" art but in this class I need projects that don't need as much one-on-one time as our typical projects do *and* that can be (mostly) completed in one class session (vs our class projects which can stretch out over weeks or months!). So, today, as we examined the many various ways Flowers have been portrayed in art, we tried our hand at these. They came out pretty cute, but more importantly, the students (not all are from our Reggio-Inspired school and are really only ever exposed to "cookie cutter" type "crafts" -i.e. Hand-print turkeys, 3-circle snowmen,etc) had a great opportunity to help them see unconventional supplies (forks, straws for stems, ) can be surprisingly good Art Tools! So, I'll chalk this project up as a success! #reggioinspired #reggioapproach #atelier #artclass #artteacher #mixedmedia #reggio #reggioschool

1077538249017134081_1100101026.caption: As I am just waking up, about to read some inspirational books, I was just laying in bed thinking.. Thinking about the people I have met, the lives that are being changed, and how much my life has changed in less then 90 days.. I always dreamt of another lifestyle, but never did I think I will be able to accomplish it or how to get there.. But when I learned and finally listen to see what this crazy business is about I quickly learn this business isn't out for themselves, it is about helping soo many people.. We are a family, we want to help single parents to work less or being at home full time, we want to help people who is working crazy amount of hours and truly lost themselves into work, for college kids that are in over there head with student loans ( been there),or to have a supplement income, to build a college fund for your kids, or what about that dream house you always wanted.. We are changing people lives, it could be financially or it could be to live a healthier lifestyle, yes we so this all from our phone.. so why wouldn't you want to be part of a company like this, that has 24/7 support, prays together, guides you, and pushes you to be as successful as you want. I can't believe by December I will be home full time, and truly focusing on what I want in life. Don't be afraid to try something new, all you truly have to do is believe in yourself and really want to change your life. Then the sky is the limit 💚 #dreambig #takechances #believeinyourself #yoicandoit

1069935734377417923_1100101026.caption: Coming home from work a little over a hour ago and I am soo exhausted.. I realize today that I am going all in with this crazy buisness I work from my phone💚 how my time is valuable 💚 that I don't like feeling as exhausted as I am with massive dark circles under my eyes 💚 all day today I was thinking I need to get home to help those parents working two to three jobs to make ends meet that there is away out, for the single parents that they can work this crazy business and rock it, for the stay at home parents that they can make extra funds just by "playing" and "working" from their phone, for the college student who just needs some extra cash to pay for their books, thinking of all the people I can impact, i really  digested and realize how much I can make a difference, and know  I am going to the difference 💚 if your not happy where you are life, there is away out, you can truly work this business and watch your life change, if not for yourself do it for your family 💚 Steve Jobs said it best: “Your time is limited, so don’t waste it living someone else’s life. Don’t be trapped by dogma – which is living with the results of other people’s thinking. Don’t let the noise of other’s opinions drown out your own inner voice. And most important, have the courage to follow your heart and intuition. They somehow already know what you truly want to become. Everything else is secondary.” #dreambig #takechances #someoutthereneedsyou #listentoyourheart

Today's photo looks in at what was once called the Hayward Army Air Field.  The Air Field was built in 1942 during World War II and was deemed surplus following the end of the war. The Airport is open to the public and their annual Open House is definitely a crowd pleaser!

1084089329104591815_1447011157.caption:
#gladtidings #alhamdulillah #goodevening In the screenshot the dream I saw. {Nb: in french I heard the prince who said "présidence" which i translated in english "gouvernance". Besides it isn't important people to know what prince said for me...so I let to be a surprise in sha Allah.} If all people were well-intentioned I yet would have told or shared each thing Allah has promised to me or to people. But I know people's heart are weak. 
The prophet Mohammed sallahou aleyi wa salam said "If anyone of you has a dream that he likes then it is from Allah. He should thank Allah for it and narrate it to others." (Sahih Al-Bukhari)

However he said also "If one sees a good dream, let him expect good, and not tell it except to those he likes." (Muslim) An example of this is Yaqoob (AS) telling his son, Yusuf (AS) concerning his dream: "O my son! Relate not your vision to your brothers lest they arrange a plot against you. Verily! Satan is to man an open enemy." (Surah Yusuf 12:5) 
PS: if people do something bad against me, you or anyone else, I will warn that it's my right (and anyone who bore unjustice) to chose to be patient in this life and to give to each person an appointment in the Judgment day. To wait in sha Allah till Allah will judge between the victim(s) and each person who did an unjustice. And if people knew well about the end of world and the resurrection.... the price of unjustice is very expensive in the hereafter. What is the best for people: to repent and to submit to Allah's will in the worldly life (temporary) or to pay faults in the hereafter (eternally)?

1154755155970496548_239317821.caption: New Year, New Perspectives ✨✨ No story today, just a quick observation: There's an alley behind Christ Church at Oxford University (which is where they filmed the "Great Hall" scenes in the Harry Potter movies, for those who didn't know). In this alley, the houses all look like Amsterdam; the buildings are really narrow and multi-colored, and the windows don't align-- they just randomly dott the facade, and there's missing glass, as you can see. Everything is mismatched, and you have to crane your head up to see the top floors because the alley is really narrow and it curves. I love it; it's the perfect metaphor. Visually and geometrically speaking, it's almost perfect, but NOT quite. That's why it rules. This is what I aim for in work and in life-- I like things to be close to perfect but slightly OFF, which is a way of building idiosyncrasy. As a result, I'll make things crooked or change the language to be just SLiGHTLY weird, anything to avoid perfect. People can't relate to perfect. Incidentally, this is ALSO the theory of BEAUTY, which makes me think I'm on to something-- supposedly, the most beautiful people in the world have NEARLY symmetrical faces that don't QUITE align. The idea is that Angelina Jolie's face is ALMOST symmetrical, but just slightly off, which is what makes it appealing. Conversely, this is why you're probably weirded out by overtly airbrushed faces or cover girls who don't have contours where their armpits should be. (Shame on you, crappy photoshoppers.) And with that questionable mental image of an armpit in mind, on to 2016: may your year be almost-perfect, but not. ✌️😉

948100310428043698_1546270017.caption: One of the @trilliumbrewing brews I got into recently thanks to @taraaa43. Mosaic Dry Hopped #FortPoint is definitely an above average #PaleAle. Lots of dank hop flavor while still being easy drinking on the finish. It's sticky yet maintains a medium body. There's plenty of juicy tropical fruit flavor but also a slight dry winey note. It's a complex #beer that covers a lot of ground and challenges your palate but damn does it go down easily. Can you tell I enjoyed it? #craftbeer #beertrade #MAbeer #drinklocal #TrilliumBrewing #Connecticraft

1095946472538524431_1546270017.caption: When you think of #Vermont Double IPAs, #SecondFiddle from @fiddleheadbrewing is likely one of the first 3 that comes to your mind. It's no coincidence that it has such a great reputation! A delicious caramel malt backbone showcases a beautifully balanced hop profile featuring mostly floral and citrus hops, with more subtle pine and tropical notes as well. There's plenty of hop character but the mouthfeel remains creamy and smooth, which is especially impressive at 8.2% ABV. Simply put: It's one of the most balanced DIPAs out there and it packs a ton of flavor, make sure to go to the brewery and pick some up on your next Vermont beercation 🍻 #FiddleheadBrewing #VTbeer #drinklocal #ConnectiCraft A huge thank you to @gmfeeny for the hookup

853990592995150737_1546270017.caption: @backeastbrewing's #GoldenAle. One of the best pieces of advice I've been given when trying a new brewery is to start out with their lightest offering. IPAs and darker #beer can sometimes hide poor quality behind bold flavors but a brewery has to have real talent for a pilsner or, in this case, a light ale to have a great taste. #BackEastBrewing from #Bloomfield, #CT has proven themselves as a talented #Connecticut brewery with this crisp and delicious #malty Golden Ale. Planning a road trip to tour the #brewery next weekend, stay tuned. #craftbeer #beerporn #craftbeernotcrapbeer #drinklocal #ctbrewcrew #connecticraft

EVERYtime I hear someone say they're "sick of seeing ItWorks on Facebook"—it totally makes me chuckle.
Let's compare priorities:
This way of thinking.....
☑You are on your Facebook just as much as I am. ☑You make zero money from doing so. ☑You are offended by Facebook statuses so much that you get super upset about it & comment rather than silently delete. ☑You share posts that you think will get you "likes".
☑Again, you notice your "likes"—let's face it, that in itself deserves another round of recognition. I've never heard anyone say, "I had 98 likes on my post today; it was enough to cover my groceries, monthly mortgage, all of our utilities, and put money into savings!"
My way of thinking....
☑I'm changing lives. ☑I get paid to be on Instagram. ☑I'm allowed to be on my phone "at work" because I work from my couch!

1034174929133815581_2098807224.caption:
The chopped marinated cold salad is such a workhorse in the summer farm kitchen! It forms the basis of so many instant fast meals. Its basically a giant bowl of whatever veggies are ripe on the farm, cubed cheese, fistfuls of farm herbs, olive oil and usually balsamic vinegar, sea salt and fresh cracked pepper. This one veered southwest with lemon juice, cilantro, fresh corn and chopped avocado-and it will find it's home tucked into quick omelets, quesadillas, on tortilla chips with mashed black beans for an instant lunch or folded into pasta, orzo, farro, couscous or quinoa for a tasty dinner side with grilled chicken or steak. We also love it tossed with arugula. So many ways to enjoy. As I take from it all week, I just add more veggies, cubed cheese and it continues to marinate in the fridge. The perfect fast food to feed all these hungry farm bellies.
#zucchini #summersquash #sungolds #freshherbs #quickmeals #avocado #farmkitchen #farmfresh #seasonaleats #farmkitchen #farm #farming #homesteading

1033247630477674367_2098807224.caption:
Up early to pop this zucchini breakfast cake into the oven. Breakfast cake around here is much like regular cake but I dial back the sweetener and add lots of healthy stuff. This one has fresh ground whole wheat, (when you grind your own flour it's so much sweeter!) oats, nuts, ground flax seed, extra eggs for protein and lots of shredded zucchini and applesauce. When it comes out of the oven , I brush it lightly with maple syrup and sprinkle hemp seeds on the top. I love any meal in the summer that can be eaten out of hand on the deck, no dishes!
#zucchini #oats #cake #breakfast #baking #scratchbaking #healthyeating #seasonalbaking #farm #farming #homesteading

1055818872560732111_2098807224.caption:

This one shown is cilantro. I can feel the seasonal shift and the squirrel in me starting to focus on food preservation, and the putting up of the farm bounty for the colder months.
#herbs #lactofermentedherbs #cookingherbs #cilantro #fermentation #ferment #farmkitchen #farm #farming #homesteading #foodpreservation

1093904190642266108_1753865710.caption: Happy news at our house tonight. The guy on the left (Ty) has a new home with the guy on the right (Jace). I bought Ty as a 3 yr old unbroke and untouched stud about 6 years ago, gelded and broke him. I took him in the mountains, guided trail rides on him, and did just about anything and everything on him that I could. It came time to move to a new horse, and I passed Ty on to my daughter, Kiley, who finished him out to the best of her abilities, but decided he wasn't quite what she was wanting either. About a year and a half ago, we sold Ty, and a big piece of my heart left with him when I watched him go down the road to his new home. But soon, he's returning back home, and this time to stay and teach a young man about what it means to be a horseman. I can't wait for their adventures together...❤

1084224825678819038_225424026.caption: One of the last roads I cycled before leaving Västmanland to head back home to Stockholm. So far my beloved home really has let me down, yesterday it was to cloudy to see the moon and the only hours of good weather today occurred while I was taking an exam... not a very exiting homecoming... 1010220578600054179_225424026.caption: A little history lesson coming up! It seems to be a common misconception that rune stones were erected by Vikings or to honor fallen Vikings -this is not entirely true. This stone is a great example. It was risen to honor a man called Assur who guarded the city against Vikings. The stone was erected by Assure wife Ginnlög. It is also important no note that there are different kinds of runic scriptures/runic alphabets. And not all stones with inscriptions or carvings are rune stones, so called picturestones are common as well. #runestone #runsten #runic #vikings #Viking #stone #sweden #archaeology

MIND GAMES.  Today was a war!  GEEZ!  I can't tell you the mind games that went on today, my 15th Day on the Cleanse.  You see, I set a baby goal of just making it to 2 weeks on the cleanse and then seeing how it goes...because 3 weeks seemed a little overwhelming to me...especially since week 3 is vegan and no grains.  YIKES! 
I woke up today feeling less puffy, a little more alert, and about 6 pounds down.  The goal was for my body to release the toxins and feel better.  It's working.  So, why would I quit now with only 1 week left, right?  Right!  But, my mind was trying to talk me out of it ALL DAY LONG.  I felt hungrier today, a small headache, and a little less energy.  But, I want to finish.  This week's theme is: RESTORE.  That's my goal.  I made it through RECLAIM and RELEASE.
Wouldn't you agree that a big part of living a healthier lifestyle is getting your mind in line with your goals?

1119719146220495815_1254872887.caption:
Happy #transformationtuesday fitties!! ✌🏼️
No matter how many months I do BBG for, posting a progress pic is always difficult to share, and having something like scoliosis make it that much harder. A recent post from @fitlifenewme really hit home for me about how critical and hard we are on ourselves and our own bodies, which is why posting pictures like this is hard. It's making yourself completely vulnerable, and putting yourself out there in the hope that your journey motivates just one women on her journey 💕 
I've been doing BBG for an amazing 41 weeks now 😅 over the last 4 or so weeks I feel like my physical progress has been relatively stagnant 🤔 but that's okay because the progress has been in my attitude and approach. Doing BBG has now simply become part of my life, but more importantly I've found balance. If for some reason I miss a workout, no drama. I also have the confidence to change the circuits occasionally if I feel like it 💪🏼 don't be afraid to mix things up if it suits you, it's your journey! 🌷😘
Side note, after 9.5 months of BBG, I'm so #readytosweat with @kayla_itsines whatever the announcement is!? 🤓
#BBG #kaylaitsines #bbgprogress #bbgcommunity #kaylasarmy #thekaylamovement #bbgresults

Finally posting a #thisismebbg after my dear friend @melissa.bbg tagged me. 
My name is Emily, I'm a transitional kindergarten teacher in Orange County, a recent graduate w/ a BA in Child Dev, and a bride to be! 
I lived in Alaska for 2 years and I learned that I have a deep love for the outdoors. And outdoor gear/clothes. REI=heaven. 
I'm obsessed with interior design and aesthetic, but I'm waiting until I have my actual home to start putting things together. 
Recently I stopped cussing, just because I didn't feel like it was natural for me. I'm not against it nor do I judge those who do. I have plenty of friends (esp my fiancé) who cuss frequently. ~I live in Rainbow flip flops. 
Bucket list goals: zip line in Costa Rica, hike in the beautiful mountains of Patagonia, hold a handstand for 20 seconds, travel to Indonesia to meet my finance's family, and spend at least a month traveling the world. 
I live for board games/family night and tend to gravitate towards staying in rather than going out. 
I'm generally a shy person with a small group of people I keep close to my heart. I'm definitely never been a social butterfly. 
I love giving gifts, no matter how small no matter the occasion. It's a bit of a $ dilemma. 
Tagged babes, if you haven't already, please share a tad more about your beautiful selves!! #bbg #bbgfam #thekaylamovement #kaylaitsines #kaylasarmy #bbgsisters #bbggirls #bbglife #bbgweek8

1125542620603486990_4822179.caption: This is a detail of a cluster of leaves and a bud of a California bay laurel (Umbellularia californica). As the name implies, this tree is native to California (at least along the coasts); it’s also native to Oregon, and there they insist on calling it the Oregon myrtle. We also have the bay laurel (Laurus nobilis) here, though that’s an import from the Mediterranean and is the source of bay leaves for cooking; rest assured, you can also cook with Umbellaria leaves, but they’re a LOT stronger. The flowers bloom from their little buds like this one in late winter in California, and the tree is an evergreen. This can also be called the headache tree, because the leaves have been used in traditional Native American medicines for treating headaches (and myriad other aches), though apparently the leaves can also CAUSE headaches, which seems rather self-serving of them. Several animals eat parts of these trees, and the trees have been successfully planted as flood control methods and wildlife restoration agents. The leaves are apparently good at getting rid of ectoparasites (parasites that live on the outsides of bodies, such as fleas and lice), and dusky-footed woodrats may use the leaves to prevent their nests from being colonized by fleas! In recent years, it has become apparent that these trees can also act as reservoirs for the pathogen that causes sudden oak death (Phytophthora ramorum), though they don’t seem to die themselves from the disease.

1019871818298822919_4822179.caption: Ezra here is chomping on a sugar maple leaf (Acer saccharum), #asonedoes  He was pretending to be a giraffe (yes, he is aware that a North American giraffe nomming a maple leaf is patently ridiculous). While sugar maples are known for producing sap that can be tapped as maple sugar, their samaras (seeds) are edible, as are their leaves. There are no known toxicities from this plant to people (though Ezra was unimpressed with the leaf taste), though horses that eat maple leaves (particularly those from red and sugar maples) can easily die from poisoning. Gallic acid in the leaves destroys red blood cells, causing hemolytic anemia and methemoglobinemia. So, if you're reading this and are a horse, please take heed.

1140809875050337056_4822179.caption: Up close and personal with another Bryophyte (moss) species in coastal California. While mosses can survive for quite a long time without water (they go into a kind of hybernating, desiccated state), they much prefer moist conditions. The recent rains here have made these little guys really happy, as they get all of their nutrients and water from the air - mosses don't have true roots. That's why they can grow on rocks and even on glaciers. This is not a glacier. We don't have those in California. We do have rocks, but this is also not a rock. Just your run of the mill coastal redwood tree.

Try this at home: Chinese sausage seaweed roll

INGREDIENTS
Crispy powder, 50g
Chinese sausage, 2 pieces
Asparagus, 2 pieces
Shrimp paste, 100g
Seaweed, 2 pieces

METHOD
1. Mix crispy powder and some water to form a paste then set aside. 
2. Blanch Chinese sausage and asparagus. Drain and set aside. 
3. Spread shrimp paste on seaweed then put Chinese sausage and asparagus on one edge. Roll and coat with crispy powder.
4. Heat oil in wok. Fry seaweed roll until golden brown. Dab dry and cut into sections. 
5. Ready to serve.

784976484130982933_436557658.caption:
We started Bend with the idea that we would create stylish and edgy modern furniture that would also be comfortable, durable and functional.  We wanted to create forever pieces that will live with you throughout your entire life.  Living in Southern California we spend as much time outside as we do inside and therefore it made sense to us to make Bend a line that works anywhere you can imagine it going.  In the last four years for us Bend has become as much a life style as it is a furniture company.  We create furniture for our homes and lives as much as we do for you. 
We started Bend in the living area of the loft where our founder and designer Gaurav Nanda lives.  It’s been an amazing space for both design and creativity.  For four years we have done photo-shoots, had conference calls, meetings and brainstorm sessions all in what Gaurav should have called his living room.  The time has finally come for Bend to leave the loft and finally go home. 
This past weekend, the search for the next step for Bend Goods finally came to an end.  Tomorrow we officially leave the loft in Marina Del Rey and head east to the Bend Goods House in West Hollywood.  We chose a house over a traditional showroom set up because Bend has become a way of living.  Bend has gone from being a line of stylish and colorful chairs to the inspiration and motivation for creating a stylish and colorful life.

1080472740276922930_199073257.caption: Does your Wednesday need some wanderlust? If so pop over and follow the travels of @pointsandtravel. She is currently exploring the South of France and is one of my favorite IGs. Get inspired and give her some love.

609216256006116491_210117260.caption:
She seemed lonely and lost in thought. She reminded me of my great grandmother. Her clothes were colorful and filled with tradition. You could see the struggles in her face. 
Right across from her were the younger men in the larger stalls that sold olives & spices. They were loud, had music playing, and we're very aggressive, calling out to anyone that passed them in the Square.

She struggles selling only 2 kinds of spices, one in a bucket, the other in a bag. It has to be so hard for her to keep from being overwhelmed by the boys in their 20's It has to make her frightened of her uncertainty. But no price is too high to pay for the privilege of your dignity. She may have a lonely existence in the Square, but I could tell by how neatly she dressed and sat there, I believe she has her dignity. I was tagged by @mitchpittman to share 10 things about myself so here goes! 
1. I studied abroad in New Zealand for 9 months in college - this picture is from Mount Cook. It was the most incredible experience of my life and part of me will always call Christchurch home. 
2. By the time I was 7 I had lived in 4 states. I grew up as a "park brat" - like an army brat but my parents are park rangers (as am I). I've lived in 7 national parks. 
3. I play trombone. Sticking it to gender norms since 1999. 
4. Climbing Mount Rainier is my proudest accomplishment. 
5. I'm one of only 4 people who have done the Seattle No Pants Light Rail Ride every year since its inception. I think silliness is underrated. 
6. I worked as a barista all through college. 
7. Tom Robbins is my favorite author - I've read everything he's ever written. 
8. For my senior thesis in college I got to go inside jails and interview juvenile inmates. It was a powerful experience. 
9. I will kick your ass at MarioKart. You may think I'm kidding but I've made boys cry. 
10. I think I'm going on a grand adventure this spring before I grow up and go to grad school and get a real job. I'm enjoying the daydreaming phase of planning! 
Tagging my homegirls @darceelizabeth and @amyela!

1136746186230276970_222235583.caption:
"Sculpture is the art of the intelligence." - Pablo Picasso

_

The mountain that needs no introduction. 
_

Located in the Black Hills of South Dakota, this landmark was completed in 1941. It cost $1 million to create - about double the original estimate due to delays and unforeseen challenges working with the granite from the mountain. 
_

The visionary sculptor, Gutzon Borglum, dedicated 14 years of his life to the project. When he died in 1941 his son, Lincoln, took over one more year. But the monument remained unfinished. With the United States joining WWII at that point, the government funding ran out. 
_

The onsite museum is really fascinating and sheds a unique perspective on one of the world's most renowned (and epic) sculptures. And the mountain is even more impressive in real life. 
_

Shot on my @vanguard_world Alta Pro 254CT tripod. 
_

#DoBigThings 
#mountrushmore 
#visitrapidcity

1055920808805613152_2010644942.caption: I would like to jump from the rooftops because I feel so much better. This week, I got my results from my bone scan. The scan came back really good.
