932790643275625593_15619124.caption:
Sacred Geometry card of the day: 
MOUNTAIN MESSENGERS -TRANSCENDENCE- 
Within this card is embedded the geometry of the pentagon. It speaks of power and excellence, of protection and divine transcendence. The natural world, with its variety of environments, provides a wonderful classroom for your connection to the cosmos. Messages come to us in myriad forms. Be advised to listen to the wind, the water, and all the voices of nature. Connect with the rock people, and listen to what the animals have to say. 
In the cosmology of many indigenous cultures the presence of the mountain lion, also called puma or panther, denotes connection to our earthly animal nature and the courage and protection that having this totem provides. It is a deep energetic connection that humans feel with the power of their animal relatives. Experiencing communication with an animal or any force of nature likely puts you in touch with a spirit guide. The power of this communication may result in a transcendent experience that defies rational thought or conventional experience. You are invited to see nature in this transcendent light, and to hold yourself in readiness for the messages that all of nature provides. ----------------- Such a powerful card for the day! This is something I have been thinking a lot about recently. bout my connection to the animal world and the world of nature. So many times, even just walking my dog in the city, I need all kinds of animal guides. Especially the winged ones. There is a whole colony of hummingbirds in my neighborhood. 
Even simply listening to the wind allows me to feel the energy of the day, and connect to the earth grids, allowing any pertinent information to come through to aid in my personal evolution and the evolution of the collective. 
Allowing the time & space for nature to speak to you will help you ground all of the energy that you feel these days. The energy is moving faster & becoming stronger each day, each day you have to realign and retune to the higher frequency. Connecting with nature and mother earth allows you to ground this energy and become a clear conduit. This makes your physical experience more pleasant!

939536159636223215_15619124.caption:
Sacred Geometry #cardoftheday 
STARRY DREAMS -DREAMS AND VISIONS- 
Stars and stars and stars… This card uses the five sided geometry of the pentagon and its ability to design stars that fracture into infinity. This geometry creates a starry field in which the transcendent power of dreams can be used to access personal stories and visions. In the center of the card we find a knotted #torus of light winding itself around and amplifying the effects of your starry dreams.

You are invited to become keenly aware of all of your dreams, be they daydreams, night dreams, or visions received in reverie or meditation. Each offers a message. It contains some insight into the nature of reality and your place therein. By dismissing or over analyzing dreams and visions, you may render them less potent. Instead, relax into contemplation of the messages you receive, and allow your inner knowing to offer insights into the experiences your dreams provide. View them as aspects of reality. They are not separate or unrelated to your physical reality; like the torus, they are wrapped around and intricately woven into the fabric of your life. 
So perfect for right now. I'm a little bit exhausted from all of the crazy Mars energy the last two days. I'm grateful for some respite, before the #plutouranussquare on Monday. I hope you all have beautiful insightful dreams tonight. See you on the astral planes! ✨🌀💤🌀✨ #sacredgeometery #sacredgeometryoracledeck #FranceneHart #SoulStarMedicineSacredGeometrySeries #dreams #dreamtime #visions #meditation #stars #starseed #Pleidian #lightworker

929974623506822177_15619124.caption:
Our #sacredgeometry Card of the Day is 41. METATRON'S CUBE - COMMUNITY - 
The geometry of this card is the place at which the female and male energy is joined to create something entirely new. By beginning with the 13 "female" circles from the Fruit of Life and connecting every center with straight "male" lines, A shape known as Metatron's cube appears. View this image as a three dimensional configuration. Within the shape, concentrate on the lines and see if you can find each of the five Platonic solids, or cosmic volumes, as we like to call them. You can see, then, how the joining of male and female energies create substance and form. 
If you choose this card you are asked to see how substance inform are working in your life and to view them as aspects of male and female cooperation. Allow this card to represent a time of balancing the Yin and Yang of your inner life to promote harmony and creativity. This may be your own male and female aspects seen as offering creative solutions to challenges are projects. You will more easily connect with the substance of your inquiry. What form does the outcome take? Metatron's's cube is a metaphor for all problem-solving, not only in the third dimensional reality but in other dimensions as well.

This card may also represent the relationship you have with others and how by joining through substantive action you form community. Community brings together disparate aspects of humanity, and when held in balance, it creates a cohesive whole. Do you feel part of a community? Are the contribute shins you are making give a life and form, pace and substance, justice and freedom to the community as a whole?

1049635305525344641_24440765.caption:
Aloha Coconut Shibuya Toast •SGD 10.80•
*******************************************************
Our prayers had been answered! Tuk Tuk Cha has finally launched their version of Shibuya Thick Toast yesterday with 4 different flavours of Mango Tango, Aloha Coconut, Tuk Tuk Matcha and Chocolate Goodies to choose from, after hearing so much feedback of expanding their popular golden toasts.

Had this amazing Aloha Coconut Shibuya toast that is very well executed! Crispy golden brown thick toast is air fried to perfection, with melted butter evenly infused in every slice of the toast and coated with honey. Generously topped with young coconut flesh, a scoop of coconut ice cream and coconut flakes that are all imported all the way from Thailand. The interior is warm, soft, fluffy and love how it slowly melts the smooth creamy ice cream that gives a cool-hot decadent feel to the mouth. It is packed of buttery fragrant and every mouthful is just simply full of coconut goodness! It is affordable and is definitely one of the best in Singapore! You can add in another scoop of ice cream for just an additional of SGD 2.50! Some of my friends mentioned that it reminds of After You's Shibuya Thick Toast from Bangkok which many are familiar with. You just have to try it yourself to find out!
#thebestshotforfood #wheretoeatinsg #tuktukchasg #tuktukcha

The French Riveria is sometimes referred to as a millionaires playground, and to be honest, that really put me off going for many different reasons. Despite that, I ended up spending several days in #Nice and thoroughly enjoying it! Not only was it lovely walking along the promenade, exploring the old town and enjoying the ambience🍷🍺🍮, it's also the proud winner of my most #spectacular consecutive sunset award. The sunset pictured in this shot was pretty amazing, but then the following nights became more and more surreal culminating in the most outrageous purple sky with orange light I've ever seen - my shots of that evening look ridiculous but to this day Nice remains my #sunset capital ☀️🇫🇷🌅. 921930691404650748_899363349.caption:
#selfie 47 of 365

I have no idea why, but last night I couldn't sleep a wink. Last check of my watch before my alarm went off at 6am was 4:20am. So assuming I fell asleep within 10 minutes, I only managed 1 and a half hours.
So for most of the day I've been a zombie. 
When I got in from work, I tried to get a selfie with the Caz-man, with us drinking our caffeine products, to emphasise the fact I was shattered, but old "you know who" photobombed the shot brandishing the sky remote. Poppy may look tired, but that couldn't be further from the truth. She sleeps like an angel these days (we finally got there), but the poor little monkey has a bit of conjunctivitis, bless her out of season polar bear jumper.
As soon as I finished my coffee, old man power came over to tow my car to the garage around the corner to hopefully get fixed this time (we can only pray for this to come at not too much of an expense). The towing was horrifying. Because my car won't start the heaters won't work. So my windows were mental steamy. I couldn't see nowt. I opened my window to try and clear the windscreen. I dint work. What's even worse is that when I got to the garage, the window wouldn't do up again. So it's sitting in the garage compound in the rain with the window open (FFS).
To blow off some steam, I hit Monday night Body Pump. It took all I'm worth to motivate myself to go, but I did. Now I'm looking forward to bed.

Today's #whatpetedonelastyear;

I woke up hungover, went to work, got cold and started watching the walking dead.

#dailyselfie #selfieaday #selfieproject #365selfies #me #family #photobomb #baby #cheeky #ghostbusters #coffee #tea #tired

1136434652734839370_899363349.caption:
#selfie 342 of 365 - 23 #selfies to go

Let it go on record that I have officially never EVER felt this ill before. This is Tuesday's selfie and I only just feel human enough to post it.
In the night I was so unwell that I collapsed whilst going for a wee and when the Caz-man came in to aid me, she found me on the floor with my boxers halfway down my thighs (such an attractive sight). She said that I had my eyes open but wasn't responding to anything (I remember nothing of this). I finally come round as I threw up my dinner into the toilet. She said I was soaked in sweat and kept talking gibberish. I was also having some crazy hallucinations. 
It's a common know fact that I don't just get ill, I get super ill but this has superseded anything I've ever felt before. This is me in one of the rare occasions I left my bed to watch a bit of telly. What's breaking my heart the most is not being able to eat and not being able to go near my little Poppy :-(. #dailyselfie #selfieaday #selfieproject #sick #ill #flu #manflu #unwell

972647514076633340_899363349.caption:
#selfie 117 of 365

Due to my niece having chicken pox, Poppy couldn't go to my sisters today. So luckily for me, I took the day off work to spend with my darling little monster.
Again, she decidedly she wanted to get up before 7am. Just as  really, because by the time I get her up, her nappy changed and her bottle made, it gives us just enough time to settle down and watch her new favourite program (which I absolutely love), "Little Princess". It's bloody hilarious and most important, Poppy loves it.
Afterwards we had a play. I chased her around the living room pretending to be a gorilla, which had her screaming in delight (I hope it wasn't fear). Then we read books for a while before she woofed down her Rice Crispies bs then has her morning nap..... ALL BLOODY 2 AND A HALF HOURS of it. I didn't know what to do with myself. I had a shower, applied my moisturiser, my No.7 anti fatigue eye stick, gunked my hair, ironed my clothes, got dressed, changed the bed cover, done the washing up, done a bit of Facebook stalking and then just sat there thinking "she's bound to be up soon". Then another hour passed. I could have had a nap myself if I knew she was going to sleep so long.
This is us on the floor of her room after she finally got up. I'd stripped her down, ready to get her dressed for the day, gave her a little wash and then pulled funny faces at her through the phone camera to make her smile.
We then had lunch and I treated her to an exciting trip out. We went to the bike shop so I could buy a new cycling top. She actually really enjoyed it. I gave her a bike horn to amuse herself with as I looked round. 
When we got back Poppy had another nap (another 2 hour one).
At her dinner time I had her laughing her head off making fart noises. No matter how old you are, we all love a good raspberry.
Tonight I went to Body Pump and struggled. I was pretty tired and I'd hardly eaten. Good news is.... I lost another 2lbs so I've officially lost a grand total of 2 and a half stone now!!!! 🎉🎉🎉 Today's #whatpetedonelastyear;

The Caz-man had her baby shower, so to get out and about I took my nieces bowling.

#daughter #face #funnyface #gorgeous #baby #babygirl

982785228004416146_899363349.caption:
#selfie 131 of 365

Please excuse my squinty face, but the sun out there today was glorious.
At work today I worked my bum into the ground. You see those big piles of heavy metal things? 
I moved them (with help from others but I can promise you I done the lions share). All our containers at work needed to be emptied so they could be moved. Same again tomorrow I reckon. By the time I was done, my guns were like they were made of stone (not very big, but made of stone).
Come the end of my working day, I was pretty tired, but not tired enough to pick up little Poppy up on the way home and give her a massive cuddle. 
When we got home we played for a while and read a few books before dinner, where Poppy proved to be a right greedy-chops. She shovelled everything I gave her down her throat and kept wanting more (including my bowl of rice crispies). When she went to bed, I somehow mustered up the energy to go to body pump. And I tell you, I don't know if it was the week off or me lumping heavy lumps of steel about today, but my god I felt it tonight. Sadly after a week of next to 0 exercise I've put on 1lb since my last "Monday night weigh in" 2 weeks ago. Oh well, one must work harder.
I now catching up on last nights Enfield Haunting. The Caz-man is cacking herself.

Today's #whatpetedonelastyear;

We had a random pregnancy scare, so rushed to the hospital. Turned out to be absolutely nothing. Then the Caz-mans mate come over so I went and layer in bed with my Uke as I was tired but fancied learning a couple of tunes.

#selfie 350 of 365 - 15 #selfies to go

Despite going to bed last night at 7:30, I've wanted to shut my eyes at every given opportunity. That bloody flu really has taken its toll on me. Luckily though, work was pretty easy on me.
I got some good news today, all our mortgage stuff is all complete and accepted so now the house sale is in the hands of the solicitors, in our case, my brother in law (the Caz-mans brother). So hopefully everything will go nice and smoothly from this point out.
Tonight the Caz-man had gone out with friends. As she was getting ready, Poppy got hold of her make up and decided to copy mummy and put some lipstick on bless her 😭😭😭😭 that little monster literally melts my heart. Although she can wait a good few years yet before daddy lets her leave the house with make up on. As cute as it was, the fact she done it just moments after I gave her her bath was less than perfect.
Whilst the Caz-man has been out I've been watching back to back Supergirl. The tv show is awful but I'm pretty sure I'm in love with the girl who plays Supergirl. That is the single reason I'm persevering with it. I proper fancy her 😍😍😍. #dailyselfie #selfieaday #selfieproject #family #familyselfie #makeup #lipstick #daughter #daddy #cute #blessher

950879911243176696_899363349.caption:
#selfie 87 of 365

Well the day started off wonderfully. And carried on that way for the most part. 
I had a little lay in in the morning. I got up when the Caz-man wanted to go to her gym class.
Poppy was her usual wonderful, happy self. We had a lovely little play. 
Then I had a swift visit from my very good friend, Dan. Unfortunately he arrived about 20 minutes before I had to leave for football.
As for the football, brilliant!!
After last weeks cup semi final disappointment, we bounced back and gave today's opponents an 8-1 drubbing. 
In the first few minutes of the game though, I rushed out to dive at the feet of the attacker whole was baring down on goal with the ball. I got the ball first, but the attacker left his foot in to deliberately hurt me. His knee smashed into mine and he somersaulted over me and was laying in agony. I stood up as if nothing had happened and he got carried off the pitch injured. I said to my team mate who was next to me (and I quote) "nobody barks with the big dog without getting bitten". Now I'm certainly not as smug as I'm sitting in absolute agony with my knee elevated on pillows with a bag of frozen peas wrapped around my injured joint. I've even taken some co-codamol, which are some seriously strong prescription pain killers. The pain keeps getting seriously worse. I can't figure out how I felt perfectly fine at the time and played the whole game without any pain at all and now I'm in bits. I don't usually wish bad upon anyone, but I hope the bloke who done this to me is sitting, crying in pain tonight. Prick!

Today's #whatpetedonelastyear;

I had a doughnut stuffed down my pants at work (a jam one no less).
And I dug out my old football boots for tomorrow's (which would have been Saturday) debut for my new team.

#dailyselfie #selfieaday #selfieproject #365selfies #butfirstletmetakeaselfie #injured #injury #agony #frozen #frozenpeas #pain #footballer #ouch

1077003053824235850_899363349.caption:
#selfie 261 of 365

I've had a busy old day!!!
I got up early with Poppy and as she was feeling much better I took her to her music class. Just like her old sensory class I used to take her to, I'm the only dad in there.
After Poppy had a nap so I compiled a complex shopping list.
When she woke up we went shopping. So complex was my list, I had to visit no less than 3 supermarkets to get the ingredients for tonight's Tapas and Paella party. So Poppy and I traveled the length and breadth of southern Essex to acquire the tools of my trade. 
As time was going to be an issue, when Poppy went down for another nap, I started to prep some of the food. It's at this point I received word from one of the guests from "Peter Powers Paella Party", that he had been taken unwell, and queried as to weather I could postpone until tomorrow. Of course I can. Only problem being, I fully intended to take my selfie during the get together so I hadn't taken one all day. So here I am pretending I like rugby. To be fair I do like the World Cup. Go Team England!!!
On the plus side. As I hadn't sorted anything for dinner tonight due to the postponement, I had to nip to tesco (supermarket number 4) to get some food. And it's here that something very seldom happened. I can't be 100% sure but I'm pretty confident that I was given "the eye". That never happens, or at least for many a year. Petes winning 👍🏻
It's well worth pointing out that in exactly one calendar month from today, I'm going to be in dreamland!!!!! I cannot bloody wait.

Today's #whatpetedonelastyear;

I got home from work and Poppy had the hump, so I took her for a walk around the park. Incidentally it was 25°c last year... #dailyselfie #selfieaday #selfieproject #chilling #randomselfie

Went to visit one of the couples this morning to "seal the deal", then popped round to see my Nanny and Grand Pa-Pa for a cup of tea and biscuits (I did feel a bit hard done by, usually the very minimum you get offered around my nans is beans on toast, oh well). After that I flew round to the fancy dress shop to get kitted out for next Saturdays murder mystery night, but the bloody place was closed (#cackmeister).
When I got home I started to watch the Godfather and now what feels like 12 hours later, I'm still watching it (forgot how bloody long this film is). This #dailyselfie is #me on the couch STILL watching the godfather.

1096773788769671276_247031237.caption: So wait, a large mammal was taken from its environment, and was then found to cooperate with humans in captivity, and was taught to trust humans, learn tricks, and be riden on. I am not talking about just orcas I am talking about horses, dogs, etc. All of our pets no matter how domesticated were once wild, taken by man, and assimilated into a artifical setting. It is not different, it just happened later for marine mammals. As much as anti caps with horses and big pets like to deny this, the fundamentals are exactly the same.  A large mammal, once wild, was taken into captivity, and after some time learned to trust humans, and was later found to have the mental capacity of learning and preforming. Just because one has fins does not make it any different. It is something man has been doing for hundreds of years.  #seaworld #sandiego #orcas #killerwhales #oneocean #ulises #shouka #makani

1092709393162710833_1684693210.caption: On September 2nd, 1945, Emperor Hirohito of Japan announced the news of Japan's unconditional surrender in World War 2 over a radio broadcast to the Japanese people. This came about after the bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki, and the Potsdam Conference, where the U.S., Great Britain, and China all issued the same message to the Japanese government: "Surrender unconditionally to the Allies in World War 2, or risk total annihilation." On the broadcast, Hirohito blamed Japan's surrender on the enemies' "use of a new and most cruel bomb, taking the toll of many innocent lives." Upon hearing the news, many Japanese citizens broke down, knowing that their country had lost. The picture above features a group of Japanese citizens listening to the broadcast, and their reactions truly show the country's grief. #japansurrender #japan #worldwar2 #hirohito #emperor #allies #history

780730481733950707_380786174.caption:
A #transformationtuesday post!
3 weeks vs. 4 weeks #postpartum. I noticed a big difference in my physical healing this week. My body feels a bit stronger, and my belly is less tender and swollen. My incision is healing really nicely. The gap between my abdominal muscles closed back together and I can fit my pre-baby clothes again. 
I think the main breakthrough was realizing that I still had my strong core muscles (thanks to yoga!). I just needed to retrain my mind how to activate them. I did this by consciously engaging my core as often as I could (lower abdominals and pelvic floor in particular) - when walking, watching TV, brushing my teeth, etc. - and in just a couple days I felt like I actually had abs again. 
This journey through pregnancy and postpartum has really opened my eyes to just how wonderfully resilient a woman's body is. It's amazing, really. If I were a guy I'd be pretty jealous ... 😜 
#LandonsLegacy

1135894784218652140_380786174.caption:
I bought these jeans a month after Landon was born. I remember how desperate I was to have my pre-pregnancy body again, and how satisfying it was to finally wear "real" clothes again. Every day it felt like my body was another constant reminder of everything I'd endured and everything I'd lost. 
With Lily it's so different - I'm not concerned at all about looking a certain way, and yet I'm healing twice as fast and feel better than I did at 5 weeks postpartum with Landon. Partly it's probably the difference of a planned c-section vs crash c-section (and subsequent infection). And also breastfeeding all day and night, as opposed to just pumping 3-4 times a day like I did with Landon. 
But maybe even more than that is how much our emotions and state of mind affect the body. I didn't really realize it at the time, but now I can see how trying to heal physically while my heart was shattered to pieces was no small feat.  Grief is exhausting, SO exhausting. It drains you of every ounce of energy you have. I remember spending full days in bed, too tired to even move around the house.

I find that I feel so much more energized postpartum this time, even with caring for a newborn around-the-clock. And I guess I can be grateful for Landon giving me perspective. Every time Lily scrunches up her face and cries, my heart just bursts with love. All I wanted was for Landon to be able to do that - to do something, ANYTHING, that a "normal" baby could do. Now I don't just get to hear my baby cry, I get to be able to pull her into my arms and make everything OK 💕 #LilyOrysia #LovingLandonsLily #2weekspostpartum

949325842355062974_1553327817.caption:
Sunny spring breakfast.

1 pie crust 
FILLING 
1 1/2 cups cooked ham or cooked sausage 
1 cup shredded cheese 
1 cup frozen broccoli 
6 eggs 
1 cup milk 
1 tsp salt 
1 tsp dry mustard 
1 tsp pepper 
Preheat oven to 350 degrease, and put pie crust into pie plate, and put In freezer. 
In a bowl mix all ingredients together until combined, remove pie crust from freezer and pour the ingredients into the pie crust and place in oven bake for 1 hour or until it's firm on top, ( if the quiche begins to get brown and it's not read yet then you may lay a piece of foil over it) cool for 5 minutes and then slice and don't forget to serve it with orang juice!!! 😉

Dreams provide vision for your future. If you don't have a dream in front of you, as a place of vision, you will always return to your past and do what you've done before. You will also always assume what's happened before is what will happen in your future(especially if it's been the same way for a long time!), but that's the biggest lie that tries to steal your HOPE and your destiny! 588593886454612945_17866535.caption: On a small sheep ranch, a ewe grew old. She no longer produced the fine wool her breed is known for. She was no longer valuable. And so she was sent to a veritable house of horrors where animals lived in dry dirt pens, fed stale bread. And every day people would come and take a sheep or goat or llama to the kill room where their throats were slit and the sheep could hear their gurgled cries and smell their blood as it seeped into red clay earth. The sheep was one of a dozen saved by animal control which only had authority to confiscate the boniest, weakest, most bedraggled. Afraid, she arrived with another sheep and six goats to @_animalplace where she gave birth to this lamb on a sunlit hill. She raised him with gentle and firm kindness, embedding in home a deep shyness of people. Her name was Virginia. She lived with us for nearly five years before her body succumbed to old age and she died in her sleep, her dearest friend guarding her body all night. He is Lenny, a lucky survivor. One of a select few born into sanctuary, never destined for the sharp edge of a cruel knife. Only by going vegan will the blood stop flowing and our oppression of other animals will end and a new relationship can begin.

967413635110025890_1427066677.caption:
We talked last week about the faithfulness of Daniel; but he is also an inspiration of courage. He prayed knowing that the punishment was death. David, preparing to meet Goliath is another example of courage. The Bible is full of stories of men and women who demonstrated courage.
Can you imagine what Daniel felt as he was put into the den of lions? Or the thoughts going through David's mind as he walked towards Goliath. But they knew they were not heading towards danger alone. "Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid or terrified because of them, for the Lord your God goes with you; He will never leave you nor for sake you" {Deuteronomy 31:6}. What are the "lion's" or "Goliath's" that you face? What lay in the paths of our children? Today, let us intentionally pray for courage; for others, for our children, and for ourselves. Bad things will happen. We live in a sinful world and there is not always a fairytale ending to every story. But I know that we and our children can have courage to face them when we walk hand-in-hand with our God.
"I know who goes before me; I know who stands behind. The God of angel armies is always by my side. The one who reigns forever; he is a friend of mine. The God of angel armies is always by my side" {Chris Tomlin}. #prayerparents #prayingforcourage #prayerwarriors

I think this was a draught-only/tasting room-only beer which I missed when it came out, so I'm really glad to have tried it. Has a definite Belgian yeast character, with a floral hop profile and a bit of dry citrusiness too. Thanks so much @bettyskingsauce! #craftbeer #fourwindsbrewco #fourwindsbrewing

1086634976214787225_1441614872.caption: Nope, this isn't @fourwindsbrewco Juxtapose Wild #IPA, it's Juxtapose *Brett* IPA! The bottle was undated so I have no idea how old it is or when the last time Four Winds did a batch of this using the name "Brett IPA". Anyways, it's probably the best-tasting IPA that I've let age in the fridge. Dare I say it still smells and tastes fresh? Of course no #brettanomyces character cuz the wild yeast strain used in this was never brett but was in fact #saccharomyces, so no horse blanket but there was a bit of pleasant astringent dryness and funky aroma which I think came from the sac trois. Also smells a bit like mangoes. Some past-their-prime IPAs I've had became sickly sweet and unpleasantly bitter with no redeeming aromatic qualities but this beer wasn't anything like that. #craftbeer #fourwindsbrewco #fourwindsbrewing

966948783384487396_1663087104.caption:
A man who was severely injured during an arrest by the Baltimore police just died today. News of his death comes after police brutally beat him, sending him to the hospital with a broken spine, according to the local Baltimore Sun.

Freddie Gray, 27, underwent a double surgery to desperately try to fix three broken vertebrae as well as a destroyed voice box on Tuesday. Even after doctors did their very best to save him, he was in bad shape. He died today after remaining in a coma. 
We have repeatedly asked police what he was even being arrested for in the first place. They have stood by the description of the arrest for an “undisclosed violation.” They claim that officers restrained him on the ground, and he “appeared to be fine” when they took him in.

But a cell phone video of the arrest shows a very different situation, one where the arresting officers brutally beat him, causing obvious, grave injury to what appears to be an innocent man. Bearing in mind that the American legal system holds Gray “innocent until proven guilty,” it is no exaggeration to say that until officers proved their case in court, Gray remained innocent until the day he died.

With that in mind, it should further emphasize just how dubious the police refusal to even say what he was being accused of actually is. A beating for an “undisclosed violation” is not going to cut it. The community is demanding answers, but the police are stonewalling us, once again.

Now, protests are breaking out in Gray’s neighborhood. “What happened to Freddie was unnecessary and uncalled for,” Rev. Jamal Harrison Bryant of the Empowerment Temple said at one of those rallies. “All of those police officers involved need to be held accountable and answer for what they did, and need to be terminated from their positions,” he added.

1044738227048921869_1773595365.caption:
The Huli of the Tari Highlands in Papua New Guinea are a group of indigenous people in which tradition is a key component of their society. The way in which the Huli practice these traditions is through the exquisite and intricately designed wigs which men don for spiritual dances and performances, and also for initiation ceremonies. In Huli society the men and women live separately because the men believe that the women are a harmful influence and a “source of danger”. Thus the society is very split between the men and the women, each of whom have their own specific initiation ceremonies that the youth must undergo in order to become adults within the tribe. 
Captured by @vanishingcultures

Setting up the #GIFTBoxNI, dropping leaflets, planning tweets, organising events, attending meetings, leading community groups, serving coffee, designing materials, running races, writing blogs, staffing stalls, giving #Trafficking101 sessions, responding to emails, brainstorming, booking venues, delivering training, sharing dreams...NOTHING goes unnoticed and EVERYTHING is an integral part of us moving forward, towards a TRAFFIK-free society, together. Ingredients:
• coconut oil (2 spoonfuls)
• baking soda (3 spoonfuls)
• peppermint oil (20-25 drops)
• half envelope of stevia
• a small, glass jar with a top

1100397918714603107_832491032.caption: I love these beautiful and rare moments, they are a gift and it is an incredible privilege to be there for them. It is amazing how the little decisions we make can lead to unexpected but amazing things. I almost went to Oceanside but I saw that the clouds were due south so to Encinitas I went. I arrived at Cardiff without a set plan, just checking things out. Sitting in my car I saw a large splash out of the corner of my eye and off in the distance. It was to big to be a pelican, unless 50 of the m decided to dive together. Alien beings come to lay dormant at the bottom of the ocean? Hmmmm....nah! A whale?! We only get grey whales through here and I have never seen them breach, my curiosity was peaked and I had to know. Squinting against the light I scanned the horizon and out of the depths I saw it rise out of the water and splash back down. It was a whale! But even more incredible it was a humpback! I couldnt believe it! I scrambled for my longest lens and ran down to get as close as I could, I couldn't contain my excitement. I was telling everyone about the whale. As I was shooting I envisioned this shot where I could get the surfer and the breaching whale in one shot, it would require a great deal of luck to get it lined up. How to figure out where the whale was though? I needed a visual cue, the birds! Tons of seagulls were flying above the water, I waited to test my theory. Sure enough, where the birds were the whale would breach. After that it was just a matter of having all the elements line up for me and I'm so grateful they did. On the beach I met a family visiting from the east coast, their daughter who is a HS sophomore just started in her photographic journey. It was such a joy to share with them mutual traveling stories and my obsession with photography. You never know who you will affect and how by being who you are and doing what you love. Be free to let those things shine though at all times, had I not let my excitement take control to lose myself in the moment we never would have met and this beautiful rare moment would not have been shared or been as meaningful. #encinitasmag #encinitas #cardiff #nature #california #fluxphoto #fluxphotography

A friend asked me for a bliss ball recipe that was date free. Scrolling back through my pics I found my lemon meringue bliss balls - I'd forgotten how much I love this recipe! 
Now I get to enjoy them outside with the spring blossom (this tree will hopefully be bursting with peaches in a few months 😊)
To make; combine 1 cup almond meal, 1 1/2 cups coconut, juice and rind of 1 lemon, 3 tablespoons coconut oil (melted) and agave to sweeten. Process until combined, roll into balls then in extra coconut and store in the fridge.
🍋🌸

961776245245267859_324689146.caption:
Back to school with lots of goodies packed in our lunch boxes. 
This lunch box has
▪️Homemade banana bread topped with fig (I have posted my banana bread recipe before, but will update through the week)
▪️Salad of spinach, alfalfa, daikon radish, cucumber, tomato, corn and capsicum.
▪️Pineapple
▪️Veggie chips (store bought)
▪️Zucchini tarts
To make the zucchini tarts I toast pieces of mountain bread pushed into lightly greased muffin trays for 5 mins to crisp up and make a case. The filling is a big handful of fresh herbs finely chopped, 1 whole grated zucchini, 1/3 cup herb cream cheese, sprinkle of grated cheese, salt and pepper. Put filling into cases and bake for a further 10 mins. I have also made this recipe using wonton wrappers to make the cases. Very popular with the boys for lunch boxes and even for a quick breakfast!

713561689412390152_324689146.caption:
I love having a vegan dessert in the freezer ready when I need something sweet or to pop into hubby or my lunches for a treat (the kids can't take them as they can't refrigerate them at school)
This week it's a walnut and coffee slice 😍
Base = 1 cup walnuts, 1 cup chopped dates, 1 tsp coffee and enough water to get the right consistency. Process until combined, press into a square tin.
Filling = 1 can coconut cream, 1/4 cup chia seeds, 2 tsp coffee, 1/4 cup maple syrup. Combine and set in freezer.
Topping = coconut oil (melted) maple syrup, cacao powder.
Inspired by @eatgoodforlife #lifeofavegetarian #vegetarian #vegan #vegandessert #eatclean #eathealthy #health #healthy #cleaneating #raw #glutenfree #veganrecipe

1115566878883113990_2064060314.caption:
"Drawing on Glass".
Post 1 of 3. You can create a fairly complicated and accurate line drawing in minutes, of any three dimensional object, by using a sheet of glass. (Picture frame glass is one temporary option available for use in most homes). Be careful of the sharp glass edges.  Bleeding fingers take all the fun out of this project. 
In this example, a decorative curtain rod, end-cap is placed on the desk.  An old clear piece of glass is held vertically and flat against the edge of the desk for stability, and the bottom rests upon your lap.  Close one eye and look through the glass at your subject. 
Use a Flair Pen, or any black marker which leaves only temporary lines on glass.  You could use a Sharpie,  but may require a solvent to clean off when finished and the lines are a bit too thick. You want thin lines. 
It is a simple and very quick process to trace all lines of the form onto the glass surface. Try not to move your head or viewpoint. Take your time, use only one eye to see; it takes less than 5 or 10 minutes to complete, unless you are doing a complicated still life. 
Once you have all the lines drawn on the glass, tape a piece of copy paper, or tracing paper on top of the fragile inked lines. See next post for more steps.  #drawingdemo #drawingaday #arttips #tracing #artlessons #artstudent #arthobby #drawingonglass

1007712151745792459_1385432497.caption: When I lived in Canada, I took a job working on a woofing farm in the Rocky Mountain weeding lettuce, bundling radishes & drinking organic beer out of jars. Probably because of the last bit of behaviours, or the fact that I lived in the attic of a self made house, or because I used to have a job breaking beaver dams first thing in the morning when it was freezing, That I got rather sick. The pair of hippy ladies that ran the place gave me a concoction that wasn't unlike what my own mother would give us. Although I'm sure there's no medical journal out there supporting the study - it works a treat for me. I got a snivel yesterday that has developed into a weak-limb, raging snot fest. Cure....according to non medically trained me, and try at your own risk... 1. Lemon chopped, 1 chilli chopped, 4 garlic cloves bruised, teaspoon honey, teaspoon salt. Pour hot water over and muddle & start drinking after 10 minutes. Key ingredient for me is optional - slosh in a good half nip of brandy & sip - I could only find Gin so that had to do. If adding alcohol, be sure your not driving, breastfeeding, using machinery, over whatever legal limit your country says drinking is at etc. Once drunken, keep the dregs & repeat the process by filling the glass with additional honey, salt and water. I'm on my 2nd glass now.

937702561027943170_186780729.caption: There is a moment every day that I reach for my phone to call my papa. He was such a vital part of my everyday life. Almost a year later, it's still hard to believe he isn't here. My greatest fear was learning how to live life without him in it. Coit eased the pain of losing him and I handled it a lot better than if I hadn't had Coit. Every day I look at Coit and it brings me joy to know that he is carrying on a Chapman family name. My papa loved him. He only got to hold him once. He looked over at me when my mom placed him in his arms and said I still know how to hold a baby. My papa said he had never seen his dad's name on paper. I showed him Coit's birth certificate and he smiled. He was there the day he was born. He held my hand after Coit was taken to Columbia and I was waiting to be taken to surgery. I miss sitting with him on Sunday's watching the race. I miss that he is not here to plant me my own row of cucumbers. I miss going to see Saturday night races with him. I miss going to Pizza Hut with him. I miss laying in the bed with him watching an old western. I just miss him so much.

@arturomorenom Sorry for not posting in the past week, everyones accounts have been hot so I figured I would take a vacation. I will start it off big with this clown, he doesn't have a lot of followers but he has more fake watches than you can put in one post. Hublot chrono with dual 60's, AP diver with shallow date window and huge screws, hublot ferrari with calendar function subdials and an AP perpetual calendar with terrible subdial spacing and fake skeleton dial to say the least on all of them. #fake #audemarspiguet #hublot #ferrari #thisguyneedstoreevaluatehislife
#morefakesthanfollowers

933768166800944458_1623508898.caption: @caiquewellington You dont see too many fake breitling hercules' popping up but when they do they  arent very good. The fake on the left actually has the correct subdials just in the wrong position. The 24 hour dial is always in the left. The subdials spacing is also awful and they mostly always put those ugly white rings on the outsides on the fakes. Beyond that it should have some sort of labeling other than just breitling. No logo on the seconds hand on the fake as well as a date window 😂. #fake #breitling #hercules #professional #timepiece #hublot #rolex #ap

902363511282003061_1623508898.caption: @carlosjeanjr Here we have a fake rolex daytona 116515ln with the chocolate colored dial. Now the first sign is the gold band, this model comes with a leather band but that doesnt necessarily mean its fake. Beyond that the 3,6, and 9 hour markers are too big and the subdials should be slightly closer. The subdial should also be just barely cutting the 2 off but in the fake they arent touching. Also the number 4 looks bad and the 8 is crooked. But this is still quite a decent fake like most of the fake ln's out there. Credit to @v_artemov_ for the good eye spotting this. #fake #rolex #chocolate #daytona #gold #luxury #watch #audemarspiguet #Hublot #breitling

976070548100280151_1623508898.caption:
@onur87_  Owns these ultra cheap fake AP's and a fake breitling montbrillant with calendar functions, yet he somehow gets 300+ likes on every picture. As you can see on the left we have everything gone wrong, twin 60's, sunken subdials, hige hand base a classic 10 dollar back room deal. Then we have the AP dual time on the right (real on top) and you can always spot these from a mile away by looking at the power reserve indicator..it is always a lot smaller on the fakes. A total collection worth maybe 200 dollars. 👏👏 #fake #ap #audemarspiguet #breitling 
#stepupyourgame
#fakewatchlife 
#fakelikes

928550954565693195_1623508898.caption: @wizzleeds This isnt so much of a watch bust..more of a what the hell is this thing bust. First of all it has no hands but yet has a cyclops. It also has a rolex logo..Im sure its just a cheap prop but I dont understand...And why would anyone want to own this..any ideas guys? Just thought I would share this greatness with you. The pic is about half way down his page. Credit to @toohollywood24 #rolex #rollie #gold #timepiece #hublot #ap #breitling

926343946135465330_1623508898.caption: @meqemeja Put up this picture of a fake A lange & sohne pour le merite tourbillon. When I say its fake because of the straight bridge I dont just mean because it is straight because the real one on the left also has a straight bridge..but most of the fake straight bridges have that braided look to them and are used on 100 dollar tourbillon watches. Beyond that it has calendar functions and a cheap looking balance wheel and movement. He has quite the mix of real and fake watches on his page, he has a fake panerai gmt 8 days but I doubt the watches are actually his..maybe the fake ones. #fake #alangesohne #alange #tourbillon #panerai #hublot #bigbang #rolex #omega

932236936097584295_44421556.caption:
My biggest opponent is the self doubt and perfectionist within myself. I have no trouble being motivated or working hard, I have trouble doing less and letting go. But when I practise letting go and face my opponent, I realise, I do enough & I always do my best. 
I will never be my idea of perfect, but I am the best version of who I am. It's hard for me sometimes to accept who I am because a lot of the time I'm focusing on who I am not. However when I accept myself, those precious moments of just saying 'this is fully me', I see everything I am and what I am truly capable of. I unleash the potential within that has been hidden by my ideas of who I should be. 
If we let go of this picture in our heads of the perfect life and body, yet each day give our best - our lives will unfold organically and we achieve more and it won't be stressful. We will become less harsh on ourselves and our happiness won't come from when we reach that goal (perfection). We will be happy regardless. Every time I practise this i am amazed at how my life flows. 
This is a hard practise for me, I fall back many times. But each time I get back up and fight my opponent (self doubt and perfectionism), I fight a little stronger. I strike a little harder. And I win a little more. And with that I feel courageous and human. Because I know that no matter how many times we get knocked down, there is always a chance to get back up. 👊👊 #fitness #boxing #kickboxing #health #motivation #inspiration #life #bodybuilding #lettinggo #faith #nutrition #nevergiveup #perth #ijustwanttoinspireyou

It's amazing how a small break in levels of water can create such a disturbance in the flow. The power that can be generated is great. 
Any small change can end up causing a huge difference. 
You have the power to change something for the better. It doesn't have to be a big change. It could be small. It will cause an impact. It will make a difference. 
Everyone in this world has the power to make a difference for the better. It's a matter of doing your part. 
#waterfalls #wanderlust #LessonsLearnedFromTravel #vagabond #travel #Jamaica #Caribbean #waterfall #bethechange #makeadifference #positive #PositiveThinking #vacation

1139350108644773368_4506218.caption:
Balance. 
If something feels right, pursue it because it's meant to be right. Trust yourself. 
If you're happy, keep doing what you're doing. 
If you're not happy, make a change. 
How you feel is up to you. As much as it may not seem so, how you react, how other people make you feel is a decision on your part. 
Our lives need to be balanced before you can achieve greatness. Balance can be interpreted in different ways by different people. Whatever your balance is, find it, keep it.

Balance doesn't mean that pieces have to fit together perfectly. There is a way to piece together things that may not seem like they fit. Just like the rocks in the picture. They balance because they were readjusted and made to balance. 
Do what you love and make sure your life is filled with joy, happiness and love. 
#travel #wanderlust #LessonsLearnedFromTravel #Cambodia #Asia #backpacking @thehostelgroup #thehostelgroup #balance #livethelifeyoulove

1022949023335430151_2025803949.caption:
💥Good morning from the team here at Fitness Phonebook!💥 A few of you guys have been asking us about Saunas and their benefits/disadvantages to your results! So here's a brief breakdown of why and why not you should be breaking a sweat;

Hitting the sauna after a gruelling workout relieves sore muscles. Saunas are also often used to alleviate arthritis, asthma, chronic fatigue, and for flushing toxins from your body. An Austrian study even found that sauna use may help to reduce the frequency of colds. Although heart patients are traditionally cautioned against stepping inside the cedar room (heart rate increases) some studies show that sufferers of hypertension using a sauna twice each week actually experience a decrease in blood pressure! Twenty minutes should be enough to work up a good sweat. And always rehydrate with two to four glasses of cool water afterwards.

There is a downfall; extreme heat is detrimental to your sperm cells. Urologist Lawrence Ross, M.D.  quotes "Although saunas don't seem to affect sperm counts, there is some evidence, at least for a period of time after exposure to a sauna, that sperm motility and quality can be affected," So our verdict? Saunas pose no risk to healthy people however if you suffer from high blood pressure or heart problems you should always consult your doctor before use!

Email us at info@fitnessphonebook.com

#fitnessphonebook #fitfam #gym #progress #sauna #heat #sweat #nopainnogain #joinus #SHREDDED

1071759138918873546_22870621.caption:
Every damn day.  Regardless of where I may reside, NY is FOREVER embedded into my heart. 
Regardless of who caused it - 14 years ago, we experienced tremendous loss in our city... but contrary to most people's perception of New Yorkers... we did what we always do when tragedy hits.  We had each other's back. Try to mess with us and/or our city, you better believe that we WILL pull together and come out even stronger. Unstoppable. That's the warrior's heart.

I'm thankful that I made it back home to my precious (then) 2 year old daughter that day. Who knew that the subway ride into the city, bumping my Blueprint CD that day for work, WASN'T like any other day. My heart still aches and tears fill my eyes for all the ones that didn't make it home. 
Grateful that we don't have these worries every single day.  Look around though... THIS. IS. HAPPENING. This is reality for folks, EVERY. SINGLE. F'N. DAY.  And we see people turning their eyes and backs on them. 
New York... the great melting pot.. I love you til the day I die.  Thank you for reminding me of humanity that day.  Thank you for reminding me that we can choose to PERSEVERE through the worst of times. 
#UnitedWeStand

1018951132172132781_1076021671.caption:
Lahmacun (or lahmajun) is not a dish that springs to mind as a vegetarian offering. The name of this popular Turkish or Armenian dish takes its name from the Arabic 'lahm bi ajin' or meat with dough. While vegetables may appear, they are in a supporting role to the meat. However if you think outside the box it can be amazingly delicious veggie snack. 
I first ate a vegetarian lahmacun when I was in Armenia. It was during Lent, a time when many people who follow the Eastern Orthodox Church avoid meat (and often dairy as well). And a perfect time for a hungry vegetarian to visit. In that instance I ate lahmacun with smokey grilled aubergine, the rich savoury flavour ticking all the boxes and holding its own against the meaty option. 
For my version I topped homemade flatbread with caramelised onions (and who doesn't love caramelised onions?!) the salty tang of feta and finely shredded mint. A perfect quick snack at any time of day or night!
#Vegetarian #Lahmacun #Lahmajun #Bread #Pitta #Khoubz #MiddleEasternFlavours #TurkishFood #TurkYemekleri #ArmenianFood #LebaneseFood #WhatsForDinner #HomeCooking #MidweekMeals

1115619257899736610_6628254.caption: A month ago our oldest son's teacher pulled me aside to tell me she was concerned about his fine motor skills. He wasn't holding a pencil correctly, especially when coloring large areas, and he was struggling with his writing. I questioned her because he's amazing with Legos; putting then together and taking them apart. I was asked to work with him on lacing cards and blocks you put together and pull apart (but not Legos) and all would be good. Shortly after that conversation and for different reasons, our son left that school and started one where he has been consistency exposed to writing and drawing. He comes home DAILY with a new  piece if artwork, or five! He is able to write his name, my name, Matt's name, his brothers name, and our previous dogs name extremely well. He is proud of his work and so am I. I've seen him write and his pencil grip is very a very appropriate tripod grasp. It's amazing what exposure, encouragement, and a little maturity (time) will do for a child.  This is his shark family. There is a dad, mom, sister, brother, and baby. He is 4.5 years old and is developing just as he should. #development #writing #boymom #mom #mother #momtoboys #drawing #love #growth #literacy #skills #gettjngreadyforkinder
